(606,	'05779',	'5779 时态 - 过去完成式\n\n    希腊文中并不常见过去完成式, 它相当于英文中的过去完成式,\n    表示在过去一次动作中完成的事件. 现在完成式, 强调一个过去\n    完成的一个行动, 其所产生的结果时续至今.\n\n    不过, 过去完成式译成英文时, 并不能完全译作过去完成式,因为需要\n    较多的字来表达它的意思. 在英文中, 过去完成式通常译为: \n    \"He had finished.\"; 而现在完成式, 则译为 \"He has finished.\".',	'5779 Tense - Past Completion\n\n Past completion is not common in Greek and is equivalent to past completion in English,\n Indicates an event that was completed in the last action. Done now, emphasizing a past\n The results of an operation completed have continued to this day.\n\n However, when translated into English, it is not possible to fully translate past completed expressions, since it is necessary\n More words to express what it means. In English, past completion is usually translated as: \n “He had finished.”; now finished, it translates as “He has finished.”',	1),
