(630,	'05793',	'5793 语气 - 期望�期许\n\n    期望�期许语气通常被用在”第四类”的条件子句（译注：就是与ei一同出现的子句），\n　　表达这个行动完成的可能性很低．在新约时代，在口语或成文的希腊文中，\n　　期望�期许语气已渐消失．新约圣经里罕见这种语气．\n\n    在那些罕见的例子中，期望�期许语气的动词不是在条件子句里，\n　　表达这件事非常可能完成．最常见到它出现在\"mh genoito\"这个词汇中\n　　 (AV,\"God forbid\"; NKJV \"Certainly not\").',	'5793 Tone - Expectations Expectations\n\n It is expected that the expected tone is usually used in the conditional clause of the “fourth category” (translation: that is, the clause that appears with ei),\n It is very unlikely that this action will be completed. In the New Testament era, in colloquial or written Greek,\n I hope that the tone of hope has faded away. This tone is rare in the New Testament.\n\n In those rare cases, the verb that expects the tone of the expectation is not in the conditional clause,\n Expressing this is very likely to be done. It most often appears in the word “mh genoito”\n (AV, \"God forbid”; NKJV “Desperate not”).',	1),
