(674,	'05792',	'5792 语气 - 假设\n\n    假设语气表达这项行动的可能性, 它可能会发生, 但是也可能不会发生,\n    端赖它所处的情况而定. 第三类的条件子句, 就是\"ean\" + 假设语气的句子,\n    或者许多以目的子句表达的命令, 就是以\"hina.\"开始的子句, 都属于这一类.  ',	'5792 Tone - Assumptions\n\n Assuming that the tone expresses the possibility of this action, it may happen, but it may not happen,\n It depends on the situation it is in. The third category of conditional clauses, that is, sentences with an “ean” + hypothetical tone,\n Or many commands expressed in purpose clauses, that is, clauses beginning with “hina.”, fall into this category.',	1),
