(728,	'05795',	'5795 语气- 不定词\n\n    在希腊文中不定词几乎等同于英文的不定词, 译为 to + 动词, 例: 相信\n    \"to believe.\" 正如英文中的不定词, 希腊文的不定词可以作名词用 \n    例: 好死不如赖活着 \"It is better to live than to die\"), \n    或者表达结果或目的. 按着先知所说的应验了\n    \"This was done to fulfil what the prophet said\").',	'5795 Tone - infinitive\n\n In Greek an infinitive is almost equivalent to an infinitive in English, translated as a to + verb, for example: believe\n “to believe.” Just like the English infinitive, the Greek infinitive can be used as a noun \n Example: It\'s better to die than to live “It\'s better to live than to die”), \n Or to express the result or purpose. As the prophet said, it was fulfilled\n “This was done to determine what the prophet said”).',	1),
