(1838,	'05785',	'5785 语态 - 关身语态\n\n    关身语态是表示主词作些什么关系它本身的事. \n    1.希腊文关身语态的意思与动词带反身代名词为受词很少有相同之处. 例：\n　　　louoo, 我洗, 及louomai, 我自己洗. 但是通常关身语态的意思, 比上述\n      还要含蓄些, 因此在翻译时, 有时实在不能十分清楚的分别主动或关身语\n      态. 在另一方面, 有些动词在主动及关身的意思上差别却很大, 所以翻译\n      时必须在主动语态用一个动词, 而在关身语态用另一个不同的动词.例:\n      arxoo, 这主动语态意为 \"我管理\", 但arxomai, 这关身语态意为 \"我开始\".\n    2.虽然在某些时态里, 关身语态和被动语态的形式完全不一样, 可是在现在\n      时态时, 却完全一样. (参梅晨, \"新约希腊文, 页50-51.',	'5785 Voice - Off Body Voice\n\n A closed voice indicates what the subject does is related to its own business. \n There are few similarities between the meaning of the Greek word and the verb with reflexive synonym as the subject. For example:\n Louoo, I wash, and louomai, I wash myself. But usually the meaning of the voice is closed, than the above\n It also needs to be subtle, so when translating, it is sometimes not very clear to separate active or closed words\n state. On the other hand, some verbs have very different meanings between active and close, so the translation\n must use one verb in the active voice and another different verb in the closed voice. For example:\n arxoo, this active voice means “I manage”, but arxomai, this closed voice means “I start”.\n 2. Although in some tenses, the closed voice and the passive voice have completely different forms,\n When it\'s tense, it\'s exactly the same. (Sammeichen, “New Testament Greek, pp. 50-51.',	1),
(1839,	'05799',	'5799 没有注明时态或语态\n\n    在Perschbacher\'s \"The New Analytical Greek Lexicon\" 中, \n    某些特定的动词在一些地方并没有注明时态或语态.\n\n    多半的情形是发生在现在时态, 主动语态的动词中.特别是表明\n   一个命令 (命令语气).\n\n    见 \"现在时态\" # 5774\n    见 \"主动语态\"  # 5784',	'5799 Does not indicate tense or voice\n\n In Perschbacher\'s “The New Analytical Greek Lexicon”, \n Certain specific verbs do not indicate the tense or the voice in some places.\n\n Most of the cases occur in verbs in the present tense, active voice, and, in particular, indicate\n A command (command tone).\n\n See “Present Tense” # 5774\n See “Active Voice” # 5784',	1),
