(2069,	'05175',	'5175 Trogullion {tro-gool\'-lee-on}\n\n; 专有名词, 地名\n\nAV - Trogyllium 1; 1\n\n特罗基利翁 = \"隐藏所\"\n\n按徒20:15, 吕振中译本: \"从那里开航，翌日抵达了基阿对面，\n隔一天越过去靠撒摩〔有古卷加：在特罗基利翁停留〕，又过\n一天来到米利都。\n按ISBE字典: 有些较早期的抄本省略了个城巿名, 多半的中英译\n本亦不含这个城巿名, Westcott and Hort 将它删除了, 因为它\n含有较不好的经文类型, 即西方经文. 无论经文是否包括\n特罗基利翁, 保罗应该曾经过这个海岬, 且曾停留过\n\n1) 一城镇的名字, 也是伊奥尼亚海一个岬口, 离撒摩岛不远, \n   在以弗所与米安大河口间的麦卡尔(Mt. Mycale)山脚边',	'5175 Trogullion {tro-goool\'-lee-on}\n\n; proper nouns, place names\n\nAV - Trogyllium 1; 1\n\nTroquillian = “hiding place”\n\nAccording to Acts 20:15, Lu Zhenzhong translation: “I sailed from there and arrived opposite Kea the next day.\nThe next day I went by Samo [there were scrolls plus: stop at Trokilion], and passed again\nCome to Milido one day.\nAccording to the ISBE Dictionary: Some earlier transcripts omit the name of a city, and most of them are translated in Chinese and English\nThis city name was not included, and Westcott and Hort removed it because it\nContains the worse types of scriptures, namely Western verses. Whether or not the scriptures include\nTrochillion, Paul should have passed through this headland and stayed\n\n1) The name of a town, also a headland in the Ionian Sea, not far from the island of Samos, \n Between the estuaries of Ephesus and Mian River (Mt. Mycale) foothills',	1),
