(3234,	'05820',	'同义词\n\n   见 bia              970\n   见 dunamis         1411\n   见 energeia        1753\n   见 exousia         1849\n   见 ischus          2479\n   见 kratos          2904\n\n    970 - 猛力, 常指压迫人的力量,呈现于暴力行为中\n   1411 - 力量, 天生的能力,一般性的用语\n   1753 - 运作, 运行的能力,施展的能力\n   1849 - 主要是指行动的自由,因此有\"威权\"的意思--或是\n           有权限的能力,或是无限制,专断的能力 \n   2479 - 力量,能力(特别是身体上的),是一种天赋\n   2904 - 能力,彰显的大能--在新约主要指神的能力',	'synonyms\n\n see bia 970\n See Dunamis 1411\n See energeia 1753\n See Exousia 1849\n See ischus 2479\n See kratos 2904\n\n 970 - Violent force, often referred to as the force of oppression, manifested in violence\n 1411 - Strength, natural abilities, general terms\n 1753 - Ability to function, ability to operate, ability to perform\n 1849 - Primarily refers to freedom of movement, hence the meaning of “authority” - or\n the ability to have authority, or the ability to be unlimited, arbitrary \n 2479 - Strength, ability (especially physical), is a gift\n 2904 - Abilities, Revealed Powers - Abilities that are the main indications of the New Testament',	1),
(3235,	'05824',	'同义词\n\n   见 bosko     的定义      1006\n   见 poimaino  的定义      4165\n\n   4165 较广义, 监督 照管之意; 译成\"看管, 照顾\"\n   1006 较狭义; 养育 滋养之意; 特指\"喂养\"',	'synonyms\n\n See definition of bosko 1006\n See definition of poimaino 4165\n\n 4165 In a broader sense, supervision and care; translated as “care, care”\n 1006 Narrowly defined; meaning nurturing and nourishing; specifically “feeding”',	1),
(3236,	'05871',	'同义词\n\n   参poieo的定义           4160\n   参prasso的定义          4238\n\n   4160 意思是\"做\", 而4238 - 的意思是\"实践\";\n   4160 是任命去执行, 而4238 是计画要执行, 且是热心的,习惯性的; \n   4160 只是生产的行动, 而4238 definitely directed action; \n   4160 是指派一个行动的结果, 而4238是这结果的范围和特性',	'synonyms\n\n Definition of poieo 4160\n Definition of prasso 4238\n\n 4160 means “do”, while 4238 - means “practice”;\n 4160 is an appointment to be executed, while 4238 is a plan to be executed, and is enthusiastic and habitual; \n 4160 is only a production action, while 4238 is a directed action; \n 4160 is the result of assigning an action, while 4238 is the scope and characteristics of that outcome',	1),
(3237,	'05818',	'Synonyms\n\n   见bathmos          898\n   见erchomai        2064\n   见poreuomai       4198\n   见choreo          5562\n\n   2064 - 通常表示动作，或进行中的任何动作，因此意为”来”，”到达”和”去”\n    898 - 基本上的意义是 \"走\", \"走一步\" 形容动作的方式; \"走开\"\n   4198 - 通常是表示行动, 有种限制, 或者明显是可以承受的; 因此常用来形容军队前进.\n   5562 - 总是强调分开, 更换地方, 而不像4198, 是外在的, 可见的动作.',	'See bathmos 898\n See erchomai 2064\n See poreuomai 4198\n See choreo 5562\n\n 2064 - Usually indicates an action, or any action in progress, so it means “come”, “arrive” and “go”\n 898 - Basically meaning “go”, “take a step” to describe the way of action; “walk away”\n 4198 - It is usually an indication of action, limited in kind, or clearly tolerable; therefore it is often used to describe the advance of an army.\n 5562 - The emphasis always on separating, changing places, unlike 4198, is external, visible action.',	1),
(3238,	'05841',	'同义词\n\n   见 ekplesso        1605\n   见 ptoeo           4422\n   见 tremo           5141\n   见 phobeo          5399\n\n   1605 - \"惊讶\",可能原本有突然受到惊恐之意,但是常常描述其他\n           不是像惊恐一样严重的情况\n   4422 - \"惊吓\", 以恐惧搅乱人心\n   5141 - \"颤抖\", 主要指生理现象\n   5399 - \"惧怕\", 一般用词; 通常指一段漫长的情况',	'synonyms\n\n see ekplesso 1605\n See ptoeo 4422\n See tremo 5141\n See phobeo 5399\n\n 1605 - “Surprised”, may have the meaning of being suddenly frightened, but often describes other\n It\'s not as serious as panic\n 4422 - “Frightened”, disturbing people with fear\n 5141 - “trembling”, mainly refers to physiological phenomena\n 5399 - “fear”, general term; usually refers to a long period of time',	1),
(3239,	'05850',	'同义词\n\n   见 thrauo  的定义        2352\n   见 katagnumi  的定义     2608\n   见 rhegnumi  的定义      4486\n\n   4486 - \"撕裂成片\", 特别描述各部分离异的情况\n   2608 - \"打破\", 指的是完整性与一体性被破坏\n   2352 - \"粉碎\", 隐含众多碎片以及打得粉碎的意思',	'synonyms\n\n See definition of thrauo 2352\n See definition of katagnumi 2608\n See definition of rhegnumi 4486\n\n 4486 - “Tear into pieces”, describing in particular the circumstances of the separation of parts\n 2608 - “Breaking”, meaning the destruction of integrity and unity\n 2352 - “Shatter”, implying numerous fragments and the meaning of smashing',	1),
(3240,	'05836',	'同义词\n\n   见 didomi    的定义      1325\n   见 doreomai  的定义      1433\n\n1325 是一般性的 \"给予\" 与 2983 \"拿取\" 相反;\n1433 特别的给予, 就是 \"赐下\"; \n1325 可能给予不好的东西, 但 1433 只有在反讽时才会用于不好的东西.',	'synonyms\n\n See definition of didomi 1325\n See definition of doreomai 1433\n\n1325 is the general “give” opposite to 2983 “take”;\n1433 A special giving is “given”; \n1325 may give bad things, but 1433 will only be used for bad things when ironically.',	1),
