(3674,	'05775',	'5775 时态 - 过去不完成式\n\n    过去不完成式通常代表一个连续或重覆的行动, 现在时态可译为 \"they are\n    asking,\" 而过去不完成式则译为 \"they kept on asking.\"\n\n    不过在\"to be,\"动词中, 过去不完成式则表示去过一个单一的事件,\n    而不是连续或重覆的动作.',	'5775 Tense - Past Incomplete\n\n Whereas in the past the incompletion usually represented a continuous or repeated action, the present tense can be translated as “they are\n asking,” whereas in the past incomplete was translated as “they kept on asking.”\n\n However, in the verb “to be,” the past incompletion indicates that a single event has been,\n Instead of continuous or repetitive actions.',	1),
