(4736,	'05834',	'同义词\n\n   见 1249 diakonos  的定义\n   见 1402 douloo    的定义     \n   见 2324 therapon  的定义      \n   见 5257 huperetes 的定义      \n\n1249 表示仆人的工作行动,而非1402所表达的仆人关系,或是2324的自愿心态.\n相对于1249,1402隐含一个受霞制的人与另外一人维持永久的从属关系.2324则\n强调服侍的人不论是奴仆或自由身,皆出于自愿,比起1042是个更尊贵更温和的字\n眼.5257则表示臣服.',	'synonyms\n\n See definition of 1249 diakonos\n See definition of 1402 douloo \n See definition of 2324 therapon \n See definition of 5257 huperetes \n\n1249 indicates the work of the servant, not the servant relationship expressed in 1402, or the voluntary mentality of 2324.\nRelative to 1249,1402 implying that a person subject to Kasumi maintains a permanent affiliation with another person.2324\nEmphasizing that those who serve, whether they are slaves or free, are voluntary. It is a more honorable and gentle word than 1042\nEyes. 5257 means surrender.',	1),
