(4850,	'04339',	'4339 proselutos {pros-ay\'-loo-tos}\n\n源自 4334 的交替型; TDNT - 6:727,943; 形容词\n\nAV - proselyte 4; 4\n\n1) (从多神教改为信奉犹太教的)改变宗教者\n\n拉比将改信犹太教的人分为两种:一种为\"公义的改信犹太教者\",一种为\n\"门口的改信犹太教者.\"前者接受割礼,遵守所有的摩西律法,以及犹太\n教的规矩.后者住在犹太人当中,没有受割礼,不过遵守某些律法,特别是\n注意所谓的\"挪亚七戒\":拜偶像,亵渎神,杀人,不贞,偷窃,反抗领导,以\n及食用\"带血的肉\".',	'4339 proselutos {pros-ay\'-loo-tos}\n\nAlternate from 4334; TDNT - 6:727 ,943; adjective\n\nAV - proselyte 4; 4\n\n1) Religious converts (from polytheism to Judaism)\n\nRabbis divided converts to Judaism into two categories: “righteous converts to Judaism” and one for\n“The converted Jews at the door.” The former were circumcised and obeyed all the laws of Moses, as well as the Jews\nwho lived among the Jews and were not circumcised, but observed certain laws, in particular\nBeware of the so-called “Seven Rings of Noah”: worship of idols, blasphemy, murder, infidelity, theft, defiance of leadership,\nand consumption of “flesh with blood”.',	1),
