(5119,	'02773',	'2773 kermatistes {ker-mat-is-tace\'}\n\n源自2772的衍生字; 阳性名词\n\nAV - changer of money 1; 1\n\n1) 兑换钱的人 (#约 2:14|)\n\n在耶路撒冷圣殿外邦人的院里,有人贩卖献祭用的动物,香油.这笔大生意\n吸引不找钱庄的人前来交易.',	'2773 kermatistes {ker-mat-is-tace\'}\n\nDerived from 2772; masculine noun\n\nAV - changer of money 1; 1\n\n1) People who exchange money (#约 2:14 |)\n\nIn the compound of the Gentiles in the Jerusalem Temple, there were people selling sacrificial animals and sesame oil. This was a big business.\nAttract people who are not looking for money to come and trade.',	1),
