(5186,	'02041',	'2041 ergon {er\'-gon}\n\n源自已废弃不用的ergo (工作); TDNT - 2:635,251; 中性名词\n\n钦定本 - work 152, deed 22, doing 1, labour 1; 176\n\n1) 行动, 作为\n 1a) 相对于休息\n 1b) 实际的明证\n 1c) 作为, 成就\n  1c1) 神的作为\n  1c2) 人的作为\n2) (正规的) 工作, 职业\n3) 产品, 事业, 工作\n4) 事情 (#徒 5:38|)',	'2041 ergon {er\'-gon}\n\nDerived from an obsolete ergo (work); TDNT - 2:635 ,251; neutral noun\n\nAdmitted book - work 152, working 22, doing 1, labor 1; 176\n\n1) Actions, as\n 1a) Relative to rest\n 1b) Evidence of reality\n 1c) Acts, achievements\n 1c1) Acts of God\n 1c2) The act of man\n2) (regular) work, occupation\n3) Products, careers, jobs\n4) Thing (#徒 5:38 |)',	1),
(5187,	'02063',	'2063 eruthros {er-oo-thros\'}\n\n字源不详; 形容词\n\nAV - Red 2; 2\n\n1) 红色的\n 1a) 红海 (#徒 7:36; 来 11:29|)\n     印度洋冲击阿拉伯和波斯海岸, 造成两个海湾, 在东方的叫作波斯湾, 另一个在阿拉伯半\n     岛的另一边. 在新约中, 此字用以指阿拉伯湾的上(北)面的部分(Heropolitie 湾, \n     即所谓的苏伊士湾), 以色列的祖先就是由埃及经此处而进入阿拉伯半岛沿岸.',	'2063 eruthros {er-oo-thros\'}\n\nUnknown origin; adjective\n\nAV - Red 2; 2\n\n1) red\n 1a) Red Sea (#徒 7:36; Come 11:29 |)\n The Indian Ocean hit the Arabian and Persian coasts, creating two bays, in the east called the Persian Gulf, and the other in the Arabian half\n The other side of the island. In the New Testament, this word is used to refer to the upper (northern) portion of the Arabian Gulf (Heropolitie Bay, \n the so-called Gulf of Suez), through which the ancestors of Israel entered the coast of the Arabian Peninsula from Egypt.',	1),
(5188,	'04118',	'4118 pleistos {plice\'-tos}, or pleistai (阴性主格复数), or pleiston (中性单数直接受格)\n\n4183 不规则最高级; 形容词\n\nAV - most 2, very great 1; 3\n\n1) 最多,　最大量的\n2) 大多数, 多半 (#太 11:20; 21:8; 可 4:1; 林前 14:27|)',	'4118 pleistos {plice\'-tos}, or pleistai (negative nominative plural), or pleiston (neutral singular directly accepted)\n\n4183 irregular superlative; adjective\n\nAV - most 2, very great 1; 3\n\n1) The most, the largest\n2) Most, Most (#太 11:20; 21:8; May 4:1; Forests 14:27 |)',	1),
(5189,	'04143',	'4143 ploion {ploy\'-on}\n\n源自 4126; 中性名词\n\nAV - ship 66, shipping 1; 67\n\n1) 船 \n 1a) 大型航海用的\n 1b) 小型诸如在革尼撒勒湖补鱼用的',	'4143 ploion {ploy\'-on}\n\nDerived from 4126; neutral noun\n\nAV - ship 66, shipping 1; 67\n\n1) Ship \n 1a) Large-scale nautical\n 1b) Small-sized ones such as those used to replenish fish in Lake Genizal',	1),
(5190,	'04157',	'4157 pnoe {pno-ay\'}\n\n源自 4154; TDNT - 6:453,876; 阴性名词\n\nAV - wind 1, breath 1; 2\n\n1) 气息, 生命的气息\n2) 风',	'4157 pnoe {pno-ay\'}\n\nFrom 4154; TDNT - 6:453 ,876; negative noun\n\nAV - wind 1, breath 1; 2\n\n1) Breath, breath of life\n2) wind',	1),
(5191,	'04178',	'4178 pollakis {pol-lak\'-is}\n\n表次数的副词 源于 4183; 副词\n\nAV - often 7, oft 5, ofttimes 3, oftentimes 3; 18\n\n1) 多次, 时常, 屡次',	'4178 pollakis {pol-lak\'-is}\n\nThe adverb of the number of tables comes from 4183; adverb\n\nAV - often 7, oft 5, ofttimes 3, oftentimes 3; 18\n\n1) Many times, often, and repeatedly',	1),
(5192,	'04238',	'4238 prasso {pras\'-so}\n\n字根型; TDNT - 6:632,927; 动词\n\nAV - do 28, commit 5, exact 1, require 1, deed 1, keep 1, use arts 1; 38\n\n1) 藉着行动完成事情\n  1a) 去做, 完成\n  1b) 徵收\n2) 行动, 举止\n3) 处于 (体会当下情况) (#徒 15:29; 弗 6:21|)\n\n其同义词, 见 5871',	'4238 prasso {pras\'-so}\n\nroot; TDNT - 6:632 ,927; verb\n\nAV - do 28, commit 5, exact 1, require 1, require 1, keep 1, use arts 1; 38\n\n1) Get things done through actions\n 1a) Do it, Done\n 1b) Levy\n2) Actions, manners\n3) Being in (experiencing the present situation) (#徒 15:29; Eph 6:21 |)\n\nFor synonyms, see 5871',	1),
(5193,	'04895',	'4895 suneimi {soon\'-i-mee}\n\n源自 4862 与 1510 (包含各种屈折变化); 动词\n\nAV - be with 2; 2\n\n1) 偕同, 与...一起 (#路 9:18; 徒 22:11|)',	'4895 suneimi {soon\'-i-mee}\n\nDerived from 4862 and 1510 (contains various inflection variations); verb\n\nAV - be with 2; 2\n\n1) Together, with... (#路 9:18; Acts 22:11 |)',	1),
(5194,	'04159',	'4159 pothen {poth\'-en}\n\n源自 4213 字根; 副词\n\nAV - whence 28; 28\n\n1) 地点: 从何处?\n2) 起源: 谁给的? 谁带来的? 谁生的? 从哪个来源?\n3) 原因: 怎么发生的? 如何发生的? 为何发生?',	'4159 pothen {poth\'-en}\n\nFrom the root 4213; adverb\n\nAV - whence 28; 28\n\n1) Location: From where?\n2) Origin: Who gave it? Who brought it? Who gave birth to? From which source?\n3) Reason: How did it happen? How did it happen? Why is it happening?',	1),
(5195,	'04352',	'4352 proskuneo {pros-koo-neh\'-o}\n\n源于 4314 和一可能衍生于 2965 的字 (意为亲吻, 如狗舔其主入之手); \n    TDNT - 6:758,948; 动词\n\nAV - worship 60; 60\n\n1) (仆倒) 敬拜, 在...之前俯伏, 郑重地欢迎\n 1a) 对人, 但是没有视他们为神明\n 1b) 对超自然界个体的敬拜\n   1b1) 对独一神\n   1b2) 对多神宗教里的神像\n   1b3) 对魔鬼\n   1b4) 对天使\n   1b5) 对复活的基督\n      ',	'4352 proskuneo {pros-koo-neh\'-o}\n\na word derived from 4314 and possibly derived from 2965 (meaning kiss, such as when a dog licks its master); \n TDNT - 6:758 ,948; verb\n\nAV - 60; 60\n\n1) (servant down) worship, bow down before, solemnly welcome\n 1a) To people, but not to think of them as gods\n 1b) Worship of individuals in the supernatural world\n 1b1) To the One God\n 1b2) To deities in polytheistic religions\n 1b3) Against the Devil\n 1b4) Pair of Angels\n 1b5) To the Resurrected Christ',	1),
(5196,	'04439',	'4439 pule {poo\'-lay}\n\n显然是一个原型字; TDNT - 6:921,974; 阴性名词\n\nAV - gate 10; 10\n\n1) 门, 栅\n   1a) 用来指大的门, 如\n       1a1) 城市的城门\n       1a2) 皇宫的门\n       1a3) 市镇的门栅\n       1a4) 圣殿之门\n       1a5) 牢房的牢门\n2) 阴间(就像是极大的牢房)之门 \n3) 隐喻. 进入或达到任何的一个状态',	'4439 pule {poo\'-lay}\n\nApparently a prototype; TDNT - 6:921 ,974; negative noun\n\nAV - gate 10; 10\n\n1) Door, gate\n 1a) Used to refer to a large door, such as\n 1a1) Gates of the city\n 1a2) Gate of the Imperial Palace\n 1a3) The gate gate of the town\n 1a4) Temple Gate\n 1a5) Cell door to cell\n2) The door to the underworld (like a huge cell) \n3) Metaphors. Entering or reaching any state',	1),
(5197,	'04448',	'4448 puroo {poo-ro\'-o}\n\n源自 4442; TDNT - 6:948,975; 动词\n \nAV - burn 3, fiery 1, be on fire 1, try 1; 6\n\n1) 燃烧\n 1a)字意的\n 1b)喻意的\n  1b1)燃起同情,帮助,或憎恨之心 (#林后 11:29|)\n  1b2)熊熊欲火 (#林前 7:9|)\n2) 使之极热,使之发亮,热透 (#启 1:15,3:18|)',	'4448 puroo {poo-ro\'-o}\n\nDerived from 4442; TDNT - 6:948 ,975; verb\n \nAV - burn 3, fiery 1, be on fire 1, try 1; 6\n\n1) Burning\n 1a) literal\n 1b) figurative\n 1b1) Ignite a Heart of Compassion, Help, or Hate (#林后 11:29 |)\n 1b2) Roaring Fire (#林前 7:9 |)\n2) Make It Extremely Hot, Make It Shine, Heat Through (#启 1:15, 3:18 |)',	1),
(5198,	'04462',	'4462 rhabboni {hrab-bon-ee\'} 或 rhabbouni {hrab-boo-nee\'}\n\n源自 亚兰文; TDNT - 6:962,982; 阳性名词\n\nAV - Lord (Christ) 1, Rabboni (Christ) 1; 2\n\n1) 我的主, 我的主人\n2) 中文圣经音译为\"拉波尼\"(#可 10:51; 约 20:16|)',	'4462 rhabboni {hrab-bon-ee} or rhabbouni {hrab-boo-nee\'}\n\nDerived from Aramaic; TDNT - 6:962,982; masculine noun\n\nAV - Lord (Christ) 1, Rabboni (Christ) 1; 2\n\n1) My Lord, My Master\n2) Transliteration of the Chinese Bible as “Raponi” (#可 10:51; John 20:16 |)',	1),
(5199,	'04475',	'4475 rhapisma {hrap\'-is-mah}\n\n源自 4474; 中性名词\n\nAV - strike with the palm of (one\'s) hand + 906 1,\n     strike with the palm of (one\'s) hand + 1325 1,\n     smite with (one\'s) hand + 1325 1; 3\n\n1) 用棍或竿或鞭子击打 (#可 14:65|)\n 1a) 中文圣经也译成打耳光\n2) 用手掴耳光',	'4475 rhapisma {hrap\'-is-mah}\n\nDerived from 4474; neutral noun\n\nAV - Strike with the Palm of (one\'s) hand + 906 1,\n strike with the palm of (one\'s) hand+ 1325 1,\n smite with (one\'s) hand+ 1325 1; 3\n\n1) Hit with a stick or rod or whip (#可 14:65 |)\n 1a) The Chinese Bible is also translated as slapping\n2) Slap in the face with your hand',	1),
(5200,	'04545',	'4545 Samouel {sam-oo-ale\'}\n\n源于希伯来文 08050; 阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Samuel 3; 3\n\n撒母耳 = \"他的名是上帝\"\n1) 以利加拿和他的妻子哈拿的儿子, 最后的一位士师, 有名的先知和先知学校的创始人,\n   他膏了扫罗及大卫王, 其中扫罗是犹太人的第一个王.',	'4545 Samouel {sam-oo-ale\'}\n\nDerived from Hebrew 08050; proper noun for masculinity\n\nAV - Samuel 3; 3\n\nSamuel = “His name is God”\n1) The son of Eli Kanah and his wife Hana, the last master, the famous prophet and founder of the School of the Prophets,\n He anointed Saul and King David, of whom Saul was the first king of the Jews.',	1),
(5201,	'04575',	'4575 sebastos {seb-as-tos\'}\n\n源自 4573; TDNT - 7:174,1010; 形容词\n\nAV - Augustus 3; 3\n\n1) 值得崇敬的\n2) 罗马皇帝的头衔\n   2a) 奥古斯都的, 即取于罗马大帝之名的\n   2b) 因英勇的行径而授与古罗马军团, 军队或军营的荣誉头衔 (#徒 25:21; 25:25; 27:1|)',	'4575 sebastos {seb-as-tos\'}\n\nDerived from 4573; TDNT - 7:174 ,1010; adjective\n\nAV - Augustus 3; 3\n\n1) Respectable\n2) The title of the Roman emperor\n 2a) Augustus\'s, that is, taken from the name of Roman Emperor\n 2b) Honorary titles awarded to ancient Roman legions, armies or barracks for acts of valor (#徒 25:21; 25:25; 27:1 |)',	1),
(5202,	'04592',	'4592 semeion {say-mi\'-on}\n\n源于一被认为是衍生于 4591 字源的字; TDNT - 7:200,1015; 中性名词\n\nAV - sign 50, miracle 23, wonder 3, token 1; 77\n\n1) 指标, 记号, 表徵\n2) 奇迹, 徵兆\n 2a) 神自己行的奇迹\n 2b) 撒旦的作为,以迷惑人\n 2c) 末日的惊恐现象',	'4592 semeion {say-mi\'-on}\n\nDerived from a word thought to be derived from 4591; TDNT - 7:200 ,1015; neutral noun\n\nAV - sign 50, miracle 23, wonder 3, token 1; 77\n\n1) Indicators, Marks, and Representation\n2) Miracles, signs\n 2a) The Miracle of God Himself\n 2b) Satan acts to confuse people\n 2c) The apocalyptic horror',	1),
(5203,	'04605',	'4605 Sidon {sid-one\'}\n\n源自希伯来文 06721; 专有名词  地名\n\n钦定本 - Sidon 11; 11\n\n西顿 = 「狩猎」\n1) 腓尼基一富有的古老城市, 在地中海东岸,\n   位于推罗北方不到 20 哩 (30 公里)',	'4605 Sidon {sid-one\'}\n\nDerived from Hebrew 06721; proper noun place name\n\nThe Book of Adoption - Sidon 11; 11\n\nsidon = “hunting”\n1) A rich ancient city in Phoenicia, on the eastern coast of the Mediterranean,\n Less than 20 miles (30 km) north of Toro',	1),
(5204,	'04611',	'4611 Siloam {sil-o-am\'}\n\n源自希伯来文 07975; 专有名词 地名\n\nAV - Siloam 3; 3\n\n西罗亚 = \"奉差遣\"\n1) 西罗亚池, 耶路撒冷的一个水泉\n2) 西罗亚塔, 可能是西罗亚池附近的一个塔',	'4611 Siloam {sil-o-am\'}\n\nFrom Hebrew 07975; proper noun place name\n\nAV - Siloam 3; 3\n\nSiroa = “Bon Dispatch”\n1) Siroya Pool, a water spring in Jerusalem\n2) Siroya Tower, probably a tower near Siroya Pond',	1),
(5205,	'04662',	'4662 skolekobrotos {sko-lay-kob\'-ro-tos}\n\n源自 4663 和 977 的衍生字; TDNT - 7:456,1054; 形容词\n\nAV - eaten of worms 1; 1\n\n1) 虫咬的 (#徒 12:23|)',	'4662 skolekobrotos {sko-lay-kob\'-ro-tos}\n\nDerivative words from 4663 and 977; TDNT - 7:456 ,1054; adjectives\n\nAV - Worms of Worms 1; 1\n\n1) Insect Bites (#徒 12:23 |)',	1),
(5206,	'04672',	'4672 Solomon {sol-om-one\'}\n\n源自希伯来文 08010; TDNT - 7:459,1055; 阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Solomon 12; 12\n\n所罗门 = \"和平的\"\n1) 大卫的儿子, 建造圣殿,并以智慧知名',	'4672 Solomon {sol-om-one\'}\n\nFrom Hebrew 08010; TDNT - 7:459 ,1055; positive proper noun\n\nAV - Solomon 12; 12\n\nsolomon = “peaceful”\n1) David\'s son, built the temple and was known for his wisdom',	1),
(5207,	'04681',	'4681 Spania {span-ee\'-ah}\n\n可能源自外来语; 专有名词 地名\n\nAV - Spain 2; 2\n\n士班雅（西班牙）= \"缺乏（稀少）\"\n1) 法国以南的整个半岛\n   #罗 15:23;15:28|',	'4681 Spania {span-ee\'-ah}\n\nMay be derived from a foreign language; proper nouns place names\n\nAV - Spain 2; 2\n\nSibanya (Spain) = “scarce (scarce)”\n1) The entire peninsula south of France\n #罗 15:23; 15:28 |',	1),
(5208,	'04958',	'4958 sustello {soos-tel\'-lo}\n\n源自 4862 与 4724; TDNT - 7:596,1074; 动词\n\nAV - wind up 1, short 1; 2\n\n1) (并在一起以致于)限制,缩短 (#林前 7:29|)\n2) 覆盖,包装,缠裹,摺叠 (#徒 5:6|)\n\n   ',	'4958 sustello {soos-tel\'-lo}\n\nDerived from 4862 vs 4724; TDNT - 7:596 ,1074; verb\n\nAV - wind up 1, short 1; 2\n\n1) (and together to) limit, shorten (#林前 7:29 |)\n2) Cover, wrap, wrap, fold (#徒 5:6 |)',	1),
(5209,	'02086',	'2086 heterozugeo {het-er-od-zoog-eh\'-o}\n\n源自 2087与2218的复合型; TDNT - 2:901,301; 动词\n\nAV - be unequally yoked together with 1; 1\n\n1) (动物种类不同,轭也不同)负轭不平均,配错对 (#林后 6:14|)',	'2086 heterozugeo {het-er-od-zoog-eh\'-o}\n\nfrom 2087 to 2218 complex; TDNT - 2:901 ,301; verb\n\nAV - Be Undressed Yoked together with 1; 1\n\n1) (Different animal species, different yokes) Uneven negative yokes, mismatched pairs (#林后 6:14 |)',	1),
(5210,	'02099',	'2099 euaggelistes {yoo-ang-ghel-is-tace\'}\n\n源自 2097; TDNT - 2:736,267; 阳性名词\n\nAV - evangelist 3; 3\n\n1) 报好消息的人, 传道人 (#徒 21:8; 弗 4:11; 提后 4:5|)',	'2099 euaggelistes {yoo-ang-ghel-is-tace\'}\n\nFrom 2097; TDNT - 2:736 ,267; positive noun\n\nAV - evangelist 3; 3\n\n1) The one who reported the good news, the preacher (#徒 21:8; Eph 4:11; posterity 4:5 |)',	1),
(5211,	'02169',	'2169 eucharistia {yoo-khar-is-tee\'-ah}\n\n源于 2170; TDNT - 9:407,1298; 阴性名词\n\nAV - thanksgiving 9, giving of thanks 3, thanks 2, thankfulness 1; 15\n\n1) 感激, 感恩\n2) 谢意 (感激的内容)',	'2169 eucharistia {yoo-khar-is-tee\'-ah}\n\nDerived from 2170; TDNT - 9:407 ,1298; negative noun\n\nAV - thankfulness 9, giving of thanks 3, thanks 2, thankfulness 1; 15\n\n1) Gratitude, thanksgiving\n2) Thank you (content of gratitude)',	1),
(5212,	'04342',	'4342 proskartereo {pros-kar-ter-eh\'-o}\n\n源自 4314 与 2594; TDNT - 3:618,417; 动词\n\nAV - continue 4, continue instant 1, continue steadfastly 1,\n     attend continually 1, give (one\'s) self continually 1,\n     wait on 1, wait on continually 1; 10\n\n1) 贴近于,对某人忠诚,服侍\n2) 在某件事持续不懈\n 2a) 忙于,专注于,投身于\n 2b) 紧握,持续,坚忍 (#徒 2:42|)\n',	'4342 proskartereo {pros-kar-ter-eh\'-o}\n\nDerived from 4314 vs 2594; TDNT - 3:618 ,417; verb\n\nAV - continue 4, continue instant 1, continue steadfastly 1,\n Attend 1, give (one\'s) self 1,\n wait on 1, wait on wait 1; 10\n\n1) Be close to, be loyal to someone, serve\n2) Persistent in something\n 2a) Be busy, focus on, and devote\n 2b) Hold on, Persist, Stoic (#徒 2:42 |)',	1),
(5213,	'02208',	'2208 Zelotes {dzay-lo-tace\'}\n\n与2207同源; TDNT - 2:882,297;阳性名词\n\nAV - Zelotes 2; 2\n\n1) 奋锐党 (#路 6:15; 徒 1:13|)\n   自玛克比时代起,有一群犹太人称为奋锐党,严守摩西律法,甚至不惜诉诸暴力\n   以免自己的宗教信仰被侵犯.',	'2208 Zelotes {dzay-lo-tace\'}\n\nHomologous with 2207; TDNT - 2:882 ,297; masculine noun\n\nAV - Zelotes 2; 2\n\n1) Fen Rui Party (#路 6:15; Acts 1:13 |)\n Since the time of Mackby, there has been a group of Jews called the Enrui Party, strictly abiding by the law of Moses, and even resorting to violence\n lest their religious beliefs be violated.',	1),
(5214,	'04790',	'4790 sugkoinoneo {soong-koy-no-neh\'-o}\n\n源自 4862 和 2841; TDNT - 3:797,447; 动词\n\nAV - have fellowship with 1, communicate with 1, be partaker of 1; 3\n\n1) (藉着活动与他人相关) 连结\n  1a) 实际参与 (#弗 5:11; 启 18:4|)\n  1b) 同情而感兴趣 #腓 4:14|',	'4790 sugkoinoneo {soong-koy-no-neh\'-o}\n\nDerived from 4862 and 2841; TDNT - 3:797 ,447; verb\n\nAV - have fellowship with 1, communicate with 1, be partaker of 1; 3\n\n1) Links (related to others through activities)\n 1a) Actual Participation (#弗 5:11; Rev. 18:4 |)\n 1b) Sympathize and be interested #腓 4:14 |',	1),
