(5562,	'04549',	'4549 Saoul {sah-ool\'}\n\n源自希伯来文<WH07586>; 阳性专有名词 人名\n\n钦定本 - Saul (Paul) 8, Saul (son of Cis) 1; 9\n\n扫罗 = \"渴望的\"\n1) 使徒保罗的犹太名字\n2) 以色列的第一个王, 基士的儿子',	'4549 Saoul {sah-ool\'}\n\nDerived from Hebrew; masculine proper noun person\'s name\n\nSaul (Paul) 8, Saul (son of Cis) 1; 9\n\nsaul = “desireable”\n1) Jewish name of the apostle Paul\n2) The first king of Israel, the son of Keith',	1),
