(5571,	'01223',	'1223 dia {dee-ah\'}\n\n一基本介系词, 表示 某行为所藉以完成的方式; TDNT - 2:65,149; 介系词\n\n钦定本 - by 241, through 88, with 16, for 58, for ... sake 47,\n     therefore + 5124 44, for this cause + 5124 14, because 53,\n     misc 86; 647\n\n1) 带所有格: 经过, 用, 藉着\n   1a) 某个地方\n       1a1) 同\n       1a2) 在\n   1b) 某段时间\n       1b1) 经过\n       1b2) 在...期间\n   1c) 某种方法\n       1c1) 藉着\n       1c2) 用...方法\n2) 带直接受格: 因为\n   2a) 做或不做某事的原因\n       2a1) 因着...原因\n       2a2) 由于...\n       2a3) 因为如此...\n       2a4) 所以...\n       2a5) 为此缘故',	'1223 dia {dee-ah\'}\n\na basic preposition indicating the manner in which an act is accomplished; TDNT - 2:65 ,149; mesons\n\nChinjibon - by 241, through 88, with 16, for 58, for... sake 47,\n Therefore + 5124 44, for this cause + 5124 14, because 53,\n misc 86; 647\n\n1) Possessive: go through, use, by\n 1a) Somewhere\n 1a1) same\n 1a2) in\n 1b) A certain period of time\n 1b1) After\n 1b2) during\n 1c) Some method\n 1c1)\n 1c2) Use... method\n2) With direct acceptance: because\n 2a) Reasons to do or not do something\n 2a1) For...\n 2a2) Since...\n 2a3) Because of this...\n 2a4) So...\n 2a5) For this',	1),
(5572,	'00034',	'34 agele {ag-el\'-ay}\n\n源自 071 [参 032]; 阴性名词\n\n钦定本 - herd 8; 8\n\n1) 畜群',	'34 agele {ag-el\'-ay}\n\nDerived from 071 [reference 032]; negative noun\n\nChidabon - Herd 8; 8\n\n1) Herd',	1),
(5573,	'00019',	'19 agathosune {ag-ath-o-soo\'-nay}\n\n源自 18; TDNT - 1:18,3; 阴性名词\n\n钦定本 - goodness 4; 4\n\n1) 良善\n2) (神的) 慷慨 (#加 5:22|)',	'19 agathosune {ag-ath-o-soo\'-nay}\n\nDerived from 18; TDNT - 1:18 ,3; negative noun\n\nConfinement Book - Goodness 4; 4\n\n1) Goodness\n2) (God\'s) Generosity (#加 5:22 |)',	1),
(5574,	'04154',	'4154 pneo {pneh\'-o}\n\n字根字; TDNT - 6:452,876; 动词\n\n钦定本 - blow 6, wind 1; 7\n\n1) (像风一样迅速) 吹动',	'4154 pneo {pneh\'-o}\n\nroot word; TDNT - 6:452 ,876; verb\n\nQindingben - blow 6, wind 1; 7\n\n1) Blows (as fast as the wind)',	1),
(5575,	'04687',	'4687 speiro {spi\'-ro}\n\n可能是 04685 的加强型 (取其\"延伸\"之意); TDNT - 7:536,1065; 动词\n\n钦定本 - sow 43, sower 6, receive seed 4, vr sow 1; 54\n\n1) 播种\n   1a) 字意\n   1b) 喻意: 取谚语形式\n2) 散布 (经外含意)',	'4687 speiro {spi\'-ro}\n\nMay be an enhanced version of 04685 (meaning “extend”); TDNT - 7:536 ,1065; verb\n\nSow 43, Sower 6, Receive Seed 4, VR SOW 1; 54\n\n1) Sowing\n 1a) literal\n 1b) Metaphorical meaning: take the form of a proverb\n2) Spread (by external implication)',	1),
(5576,	'00071',	'71 ago {ag\'-o}\n\n字根型; 动词\n\n钦定本 - bring 45, lead 12, go 7, bring forth 2, misc 5, vr bring 1; 72\n\n1) 从一个地点引往另一地点\n   1a) 引导, 带领\n   1b) 携带\n2) 逮捕, 带走\n3) (道德与灵性上的) 带领, 指引, 鼓励\n4) 度过\n5) (离开一个地点) 去',	'71 ago {ag\'-o}\n\nroot; verb\n\nQindingben - bring 45, lead 12, go 7, bring forth 2, misc 5, vr bring 1; 72\n\n1) Lead from one location to another\n 1a) guide, lead\n 1b) Carry\n2) Arrest, take away\n3) Lead, guide, and encourage (moral and spiritual)\n4) Spend\n5) Go (leave a place)',	1),
(5577,	'00994',	'994 boao {bo-ah\'-o}\n\n显然是一个基本字的延长型; TDNT - 1:625,108; 动词\n\n钦定本 - cry 11; 11\n\n1) 呼叫, 呐喊\n   1a) 充满感情成分的; 喜乐的\n   1b) 陈情或悲伤的呼喊\n   1c) 严肃的宣告\n\n同义词 见 05823',	'994 boao {bo-ah\'-o}\n\nApparently an extension of a basic word; TDNT - 1:625 ,108; verb\n\nQindingben - cry 11; 11\n\n1) Call, shout\n 1a) full of emotion; joyful\n 1b) Clichés or cries of sadness\n 1c) Serious pronouncements\n\nSee 05823 for synonyms',	1),
(5578,	'01249',	'1249 diakonos {dee-ak\'-on-os}\n\n可能源自一已不使用的 diako (\"跑腿办事\", 参 01377); \n   TDNT - 2:88,152; 阳/阴性名词\n\n钦定本 - minister 20, servant 8, deacon 3; 31\n\n1) 执行他人的命令的人, 尤其指其主人的命令; 仆役, 随从, 代理人\n2) 助手\n\n其同义词, 见 05834',	'1249 diakonos {dee-ak\'-on-os}\n\nmay have originated from a disused diako (“running errands”, see 01377); \n TDNT - 2:88 ,152; masculine/negative noun\n\nQindingben - 20, servant 8, deacon 3; 31\n\n1) A person who carries out the orders of others, in particular those of his master; servant, entourage, agent\n2) Assistant\n\nFor synonyms, see 05834',	1),
(5579,	'00169',	'169 akathartos {ak-ath\'-ar-tos}\n\n源自 01 (当成一个否定的质词/语助词) 以及 可能衍生自 02508 的字\n   (\"洁净\"的意思); TDNT - 3:427,381; 形容词\n\n钦定本 - unclean 28, foul 2; 30\n\n1) (见不了神的) 不洁, 不纯净\n2) 道德上的不纯洁',	'169 akathartos {ak-ath\'-ar-tos}\n\nWords derived from 01 (as a negative qualifier/slang auxiliary) and possibly derived from 02508\n (meaning “clean”); TDNT - 3:427,381; adjective\n\nChinding Book - unclean 28, foul 2; 30\n\n1) (Can\'t see God\'s) unclean, impure\n2) Moral impure',	1),
(5580,	'01330',	'1330 dierchomai {dee-er\'-khom-ahee}\n\n源于 01223 和 02064; TDNT - 2:676,257; 动词\n\n钦定本 - pass 8, pass through 7, go 7, go over 3, go through 2,\n     walk 2, misc 13, vr to go 1; 43\n\n1) 经历, 经过\n   1a) 行过, 走过一个旅途, 经过一个地方\n   1b) 行过穿越某地的路途, 走过, 经过, 行经某个区域  \n2) (通过阻碍) 深入, 穿透',	'1330 dierchomai {dee-er\'-khom-ahee}\n\nfrom 01223 and 02064; TDNT - 2:676,257; verb\n\nAdoption Book - pass 8, pass through 7, go 7, go over 3, go through 2,\n walk 2, misc 13, vr to go 1; 43\n\n1) Experiences, experiences\n 1a) Walked, traveled on a journey, passed a place\n 1b) Traveled through a certain place, walked, passed, traveled through an area \n2) deep, penetrating (through obstruction)',	1),
(5581,	'02064',	'2064 erchomai {er\'-khom-ahee}\n\n动词主要以关身语态形式出现 (只有现在式和不完成式,\n   其他语态的关身形，则以 eleuthomai {el-yoo\'-thom-ahee},\n   或主动形 eltho {el\'-tho} 出现; TDNT - 2:666,257; 动词\n\n钦定本 - come 616, go 13, misc 13, vr come 1; 643\n\n1) 来\n2) 去\n3) 被带着 (#可 4:21; 罗 7:9|)\n4) (发生) 来临\n  \n同义词见 05818',	'2064 erchomai {er\'-khom-ahee}\n\nThe verb appears mainly in the form of a closed voice (only present and incomplete,\n Other voices are closed in the form of eleuthomai {el-yoo\'-thom-ahee},\n or the active form eltho {el\'-tho} appears; TDNT - 2:666 ,257; verb\n\nChindingben - come 616, go 13, misc 13, vr come 1; 643\n\n1) Come\n2) Go\n3) Be carried (#可 4:21; Romans 7:9 |)\n4) (Occurrence) Coming\n \nSee 05818 for synonyms',	1),
(5582,	'02095',	'2095 eu {yoo}\n\neus (好) 的中性字; 副词\n\n钦定本 - well 3, well done 2, good 1; 6\n\n1) 好\n2) (实名词作惊叹词) 做得好!',	'2095 eu {yoo}\n\nNeutral words for eus (good); adverb\n\nQindingben - well 3, well done 2, good 1; 6\n\n1) OK\n2) (real noun for exclamation) Well done!',	1),
(5583,	'02097',	'2097 euaggelizo {yoo-ang-ghel-id\'-zo}\n\n源于 02095 和 032; TDNT - 2:707,*; 动词\n\n钦定本 - preach 23, preach the Gospel 22, bring good tidings 2,\n     show glad tidings 2, bring glad tidings 1, declare 1,\n     declare glad tidings 1, misc 3; 55\n\n1) 带来好消息, 宣告好消息',	'2097 euaggelizo {yoo-ang-ghel-id\'-zo}\n\nFrom 02095 and 032; TDNT - 2:707, *; verb\n\nChinding Book - preach 23, preach the Gospel 22, bring good tidings 2,\n show glad tidings 2, bring glad tidings 1, declare 1,\n declare glad tidings 1, misc 3; 55\n\n1) Bring good news and announce good news',	1),
(5584,	'02513',	'2513 katharos {kath-ar-os\'}\n\n找不到和其相近的字; TDNT - 3:413,381; 形容词\n\n钦定本 - pure 17, clean 10, clear 1; 28\n\n1) 洁净的, 纯洁的\n   1a) 不当性行为上\n   1b) 礼仪上\n   1c) 道德灵性上\n  \n其同义词, 见 05840',	'2513 katharos {kath-ar-os\'}\n\nCan\'t find a word similar to it; TDNT - 3:413,381; adjective\n\nDefined Book - pure 17, clean 10, clear 1; 28\n\n1) clean, pure\n 1a) Sexual misconduct\n 1b) Etiquette\n 1c) Morally and spiritually\n \nFor synonyms, see 05840',	1),
(5585,	'04151',	'4151 pneuma {pnyoo\'-mah}\n\n源自 04154; TDNT - 6:332,876; 中性名词\n\n钦定本 - Spirit 111, Holy Ghost 89, Spirit (of God) 13,\n     Spirit (of the Lord) 5, (My) Spirit 3, Spirit (of truth) 3,\n     Spirit (of Christ) 2, human (spirit) 49, (evil) spirit 47,\n     spirit (general) 26, spirit 8, (Jesus\' own) spirit 6,\n     (Jesus\' own) ghost 2, misc 21; 385\n\n1) 吹送, 呼吸\n   1a) 风\n   1b) 吹气, 吐气, 呼吸\n2) (将生命律动赋予身体) 灵\n3) (人的性情之一部分) 灵\n   3a) 与\"肉体\"连用的时候, 表达非物质层面\n   3b) 感觉, 意志, 想法之来源\n   3c) 灵性的状态, 心志\n4) 物界看不见的个别灵体\n   4a) 善良的\n   4b) 邪恶的\n5) 神的灵\n6) 神的灵 (彰显于神的子民或某些特定人)',	'4151 pneuma {pnyoo\'-mah}\n\nFrom 04154; TDNT - 6:332 ,876; neutral noun\n\nAdorned Book - Spirit 111, Holy Ghost 89, Spirit (of God) 13,\n Spirit (of the Lord) 5, (My) Spirit 3, Spirit (of truth) 3,\n Spirit (of Christ) 2, human (spirit) 49, (evil) spirit 47,\n spirit (general) 26, spirit 8, (Jesus\' own) spirit 6,\n (Jesus\' own) ghost 2, misc 21; 385\n\n1) Blow, breathe\n 1a) wind\n 1b) Blow, exhale, breathe\n2) Spirit (giving the rhythm of life to the body)\n3) Spirit (part of the human temperament)\n 3a) When used in conjunction with “flesh”, express the immaterial aspect\n 3b) The source of feelings, will, and ideas\n 3c) State of Spirituality, Mind\n4) Individual spirits invisible to the physical world\n 4a) Kind\n 4b) Wicked\n5) God\'s Spirit\n6) The Spirit of God (revealed to God\'s people or certain specific persons)',	1),
(5586,	'05456',	'5456 phone {fo-nay\'}\n\n可能近似于 05316 (取其\"揭露\"之意); TDNT - 9:278,1287; 阴性名词\n \n钦定本 - voice 131, sound 8, be noised abroad + 1096 1, noise 1; 141\n\n1) 声音, 调子, 噪音\n2) 声音\n   2a) 言词, 呼声\n3) 语言 (#林前 14:10; 彼后 2:16|)',	'5456 phone {fo-nay\'}\n\nMay approximate 05316 (meaning “reveal”); TDNT - 9:278 ,1287; negative noun\n \nChin Jung Hon - voice 131, sound 8, be noised abroad+1096 1, noise 1; 141\n\n1) Sound, tone, noise\n2) Sound\n 2a) Words, cries\n3) Language (#林前 14:10; Hereafter 2:16 |)',	1),
(5587,	'01169',	'1169 deilos {di-los\'}\n\n源自 deos (恐惧); 形容词\n\n钦定本 - fearful 3; 3\n\n1) 胆怯的, 害怕的 (#太 8:26; 可 4:40; 启 21:8|)',	'1169 deilos {di-los\'}\n\nDerived from deos (fear); adjective\n\nConfinement book - fearful 3; 3\n\n1) The timid, fearful (#太 8:26; May 4:40; Rev. 21:8 |)',	1),
(5588,	'00928',	'928 basanizo {bas-an-id\'-zo}\n\n源自 0931; TDNT - 1:561,96; 动词\n\n钦定本 - torment 8, pain 1, toss 1, vex 1, toil 1; 12\n\n1) 折磨, 骚扰',	'928 basanizo {bas-an-id\'-zo}\n\nFrom 0931; TDNT - 1:561,96; verb\n\nTORMENT 8, PAIN 1, TOSS 1, VEX 1, TOIL 1; 12\n\n1) Tortured, harassed',	1),
(5589,	'00308',	'308 anablepo {an-ab-lep\'-o}\n\n源自 303 and 991; 动词\n\nAV - receive sight 15, look up 9, look 1, see 1; 26\n\n1) 仰看\n2) 恢复视力',	'308 anablepo {an-ab-lep\'-o}\n\nDerived from 303 and 991; verbs\n\nAV - receive sight 15, look up 9, look 1, see 1; 26\n\n1) Look up\n2) Restore eyesight',	1),
(5590,	'02324',	'2324 therapon {ther-ap\'-ohn}\n\n显然是一个衍生自 02330 的基本型的字 (该字在其他地方已不使用) 的分词;\n   TDNT - 3:132,331; 阳性名词\n\n钦定本 - servant 1; 1\n\n1) (礼仪中的) 随从, 仆人, 助手 (#来 3:5|)\n\n其同义字, 见 05834',	'2324 therapon {ther-ap\'-ohn}\n\napparently a participle derived from the basic type 02330 (which is no longer used elsewhere);\n TDNT - 3:132 ,331; masculine noun\n\nThe definitive book - servant 1; 1\n\n1) The (liturgical) entourage, servant, assistant (#来 3:5 |)\n\nFor synonyms, see 05834',	1),
(5591,	'03886',	'3886 paraluo {par-al-oo\'-o}\n\n源于 03844 和 03089; 动词\n\n钦定本 - sick of the palsy 2, taken with palsy 2, feeble 1; 5\n\n1) 松开, 使变弱, 使无力',	'3886 paraluo {par-al-oo\'-o}\n\nFrom 03844 and 03089; verbs\n\nChindingben - Sick of the Palsy 2, Taken with Palsy 2, Feeble 1; 5\n\n1) Loosen, weaken, make weak',	1),
(5592,	'05346',	'5346 phemi {fay-mee\'}\n\n正确地, 与 05457 的字根 和 05316 相同; 动词\n\n钦定本 - say 57, affirm 1; 58\n\n1) 说, 确认\n2) 作解释',	'5346 phemi {fay-mee\'}\n\nCorrectly, the root of 05457 is the same as 05316; the verb\n\nAffirmative text - say 57, affirm 1; 58\n\n1) Say, confirm\n2) Explain',	1),
(5593,	'05457',	'5457 phos {foce}\n\n源于一已不使用的字 phao (\"光照\"或\"使明显\", 尤其指用光线, 参见 05316, 05346);\n   TDNT - 9:310,1293; 中性名词\n\n钦定本 - light 68, fire 2; 70\n\n1) 光\n   1a) 物质界的\n   1b) 超自然界的\n       1b1) 属神的范畴与元素\n       1b2) 人类心灵的启蒙\n       1b3) 有此光照的人, 或带来这种光照的人\n       1b4) 被属天的光照亮或充满的人\n2) 灯, 火把, 灯笼\n\n同义词 见 05817',	'5457 phos {foce}\n\nDerived from an obsolete word phao (“illuminating” or “making visible”, especially for the use of light, see 05316, 05346);\n TDNT - 9:310 ,1293; neutral noun\n\nThe definitive book - light 68, fire 2; 70\n\n1) Light\n 1a) of the physical world\n 1b) Supernatural\n 1b1) Scope and Elements of God\n 1b2) Enlightenment of the human mind\n 1b3) The person who has this light, or the person who brings this light\n 1b4) People who are illuminated or filled with the light of the heavens\n2) Lamps, torches, lanterns\n\nSee 05817 for synonyms',	1),
(5594,	'05490',	'5490 chasma {khas\'-mah}\n\n源于一已不使用的字根 chao (张口, 呵欠) 之一型; 中性名词 \n\n钦定本 - gulf 1; 1\n\n1) 字意: 呵欠 \n2) 裂口 (#路 16:26|)',	'5490 chasma {khas\'-mah}\n\nA neuter noun derived from a disused root chao (open mouth, yawn) \n\nConfinement Book - gulf 1; 1\n\n1) Character meaning: yawn \n2) Rift (#路 16:26 |)',	1),
(5595,	'00008',	'8 Abiathar {ab-ee-ath\'-ar}\n\n源自希伯来文 054; 阳性专有名词\n\n钦定本 - Abiathar 1; 1\n\n亚比亚他 = \"富裕的父\"\n1)大祭司的名字 (#可 2:26|)',	'8 Abiathar {ab-ee-ath\'-ar}\n\nDerived from Hebrew 054; proper noun for masculinity\n\nThe definitive book - Abiathar 1; 1\n\nAbyatha = “rich father”\n1) Name of the High Priest (#可 2:26 |)',	1),
(5596,	'00917',	'917 bareos {bar-eh\'-oce}\n\n源自 0926; 副词\n\n钦定本 - dully 2; 2\n\n1) 困难地 (#太 13:15; 徒 28:27|)',	'917 bareos {bar-eh\'-oce}\n\nDerived from 0926; adverb\n\nAdmiration Book - Dully 2; 2\n\n1) Difficult (#太 13:15; Acts 28:27 |)',	1),
(5597,	'00921',	'921 Barnabas {bar-nab\'-as}\n\n源自亚兰文<WH01247>与<WH05029>; 阳性专有名词 人名\n\n钦定本 - Barnabas 29; 29\n\n巴拿巴 = \"劝慰之子\"\n1) 来自居比路的利未人, 名叫约瑟 (#徒 4:36|), 是保罗的亲密同工',	'921 Barnabas {bar-nab\'-as}\n\nDerived from Aramaic with; masculine proper noun person name\n\nThe definitive book - Barnabas 29; 29\n\nBarnabas = “Son of Condolence”\n1) A Levite from Gubilus, named Joseph (#徒 4:36 |), was a close co-worker of Paul',	1),
(5598,	'00931',	'931 basanos {bas\'-an-os}\n\n有些微可能与 0939 同源 (取其\"到底部\"之意); TDNT - 1:561,96; 阳性名词\n\n钦定本 - torment 3; 3\n\n1) 折磨, 拷打 (#路 16:23,28|)\n2) 剧痛 (#太 4:24|)',	'931 basanos {bas\'-an-os}\n\nSome microelements may have the same origin as 0939 (meaning “to the bottom”); TDNT - 1:561 ,96; positive nouns\n\nChinding Book - torment 3; 3\n\n1) Tortured, Tortured (#路 16:23 ,28|)\n2) Severe pain (#太 4:24 |)',	1),
