(5802,	'02250',	'2250 hemera {hay-mer\'-ah}\n\n源于 (加上 5610 的意义) hemai (坐下,近似于 1476 的字源)的衍生字,\n其意为温驯的, 亦即 柔和的;TDNT - 2:943,309; 阴性名词\n\nAV - day 355, daily + 2596 15, time 3, not tr 2, misc 14; 389\n\n1) 一天, 一日 \n2) 法定的一天\n3) 为特别目的所定的一天 (例:审判的日子)\n4) 时间',	'2250 hemera {hay-mer\'-ah}\n\nDerived from (plus the meaning of 5610) hemai (sit down, approximating the origin of 1476)\nMeans tame, that is, gentle; TDNT - 2:943 ,309; negative noun\n\nAV - day 355, daily + 2596 15, time 3, not tr 2, misc 14; 389\n\n1) One day, one day \n2) Statutory day\n3) A day designated for a special purpose (example: the day of the trial)\n4) Time',	1),
