(5806,	'01994',	'1994 epistrepho {ep-ee-stref\'-o}\n\n源于 1909 和 4762; TDNT - 7:722,1093; 动词\n\nAV - turn 16, be converted 6, return 6, turn about 4,\n     turn again 3, misc 4; 39\n\n1) (回到原点) 回转, 回返\n2) (改变方向) 转向 \n3) (改变人的信仰和行为) (及物动词) 扭转\n4) (改变人的心意或行动,或好或坏) (不及物动词) 转变, 回转 \n  ',	'1994 epistrepho {ep-ee-stref\'-o}\n\nFrom 1909 and 4762; TDNT - 7:722 ,1093; verb\n\nAV - turn 16, be turned 6, return 6, turn about 4,\n turn again 3, misc 4; 39\n\n1) (back to origin) rotation, return\n2) Turn (change direction) \n3) (change people\'s beliefs and behavior) (transitive verb) reverse\n4) (change a person\'s mind or action, or good or bad) (intransitive verb) transform, turn',	1),
(5807,	'02060',	'2060 Hermes {her-mace\'}\n\n可能源自 2046; 阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Mercurius 1, Hermes a Christian 1; 2\n\n希耳米或黑米 = \"众神的使者\"\n1) 希腊神,相当于罗马的莫丘里神 (#徒 14:12|)\n2) 某位基督徒 (#罗 16:14|)',	'2060 Hermes {her-mace\'}\n\nPossibly derived from 2046; masculine proper noun\n\nAV - Mercurius 1, Hermes a Christian 1; 2\n\nHirmi or Black Rice = “Messenger of the Gods”\n1) Greek god, equivalent to the Roman god Mochuri (#徒 14:12 |)\n2) A Christian (#罗 16:14 |)',	1),
(5808,	'02087',	'2087 heteros {het\'-er-os}, a, on\n\n字源不详; TDNT - 2:702,265; 形容词\n\nAV - another 43, other 42, other thing 3, some 2, next day 2, misc 7; 99\n\n1) 另外, 另一个, 其他的, 不同的\n  1a) 指数量上\n    1a1) 指相对于前面已提到, 数算过的人或事之外一些人或事\n    1a2) 指两者中的另一个\n  1b) 指质量上\n    1b1) 另一种: 亦即指和前面所提的具有不同的本质, 型式, 种类; 不同的\n\n其同义字, 见 5806',	'2087 heteros {het\'-er-os}, a, on\n\nEtymology unknown; TDNT - 2:702 ,265; adjective\n\nAV - another 43, other 42, other thing 3, some 2, next day 2, misc 7; 99\n\n1) In addition, another, other, different\n 1a) refers to the quantity\n 1a1) refers to a number of people or things other than those already mentioned and counted\n 1a2) refers to the other of the two\n 1b) refers to quality\n 1b1) Another type: that is, having a different nature, type, type from the one mentioned earlier; different\n\nFor synonyms, see 5806',	1),
(5809,	'02147',	'2147 heurisko {hyoo-ris\'-ko}\n\n基础字 heuro {hyoo\'-ro} 的扩张型, (和同出于 heureo {hyoo-reh\'-o} 的另一型)\n用在除了现在式和过去不完成式外之所有时态中; TDNT - 2:769,*; 动词\n\nAV - find 174, misc 4; 178\n\n1) 发现, 找到\n 1a) 刻意寻找\n 1b) 无意间发现, 偶遇\n2) 经询问, 思考, 试验, 检视, 观察而发现\n3) 给自己找到, 获取, 得到 (达到某种状况 )',	'2147 heurisko {hyoo-ris\'-ko}\n\nExpanded form of the base word heuro {hyoo\'-ro}, (and another type from heureo {hyoo-reh\'-o})\nUsed in all tenses except present and past incomplete; TDNT - 2:769, *; verb\n\nAV - find 174, misc 4; 178\n\n1) Discover, find\n 1a) Deliberately looking\n 1b) Unintentional discovery, chance encounter\n2) Discovered by inquiry, reflection, testing, inspection, observation\n3) Find, get, get (reach a certain condition) for yourself',	1),
