(5811,	'01941',	'1941 epikaleomai {ep-ee-kal-eh\'-om-ahee}\n\n源于 1909 和 2564 的关身语态; TDNT - 3:496,*; 动词\nAV - call on 7, be (one\'s) surname 6, be surnamed 5, call upon 4,\n     appeal unto 4, call 4, appeal to 1, appeal 1; 32\n\n1) (向神) 呼求, 呼叫\n2) 称呼, 命名\n3) 上诉\n4) 传唤某人作证 (#林后 1:23|)',	'1941 epikaleomai {ep-ee-kal-eh\'-om-ahee}\n\nTDNT - 3:496, *; verb from 1909 and 2564\nAV - call on 7, be (one\'s) surnamed 6, be surnamed 5, call upon 4,\n appeal to 4, call 4, appeal to 1, appeal 1; 32\n\n1) Call (to God), call\n2) Name, name\n3) Appeals\n4) Summon someone to testify (#林后 1:23 |)',	1),
(5812,	'02387',	'2387 Iambres {ee-am-brace\'}\n\n源自埃及文; TDNT - 3:192,344; 阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Jambres 1; 1\n\n佯庇 = \"口吐白沫的巫医\"\n\n1) 烊庇与雅尼是两名埃及法师,在法老面前模仿亚伦\n   所行的神迹 (#提后 3:8|)',	'2387 Iambres {ee-am-brace\'}\n\nDerived from Egyptian; TDNT - 3:192 ,344; positive proper noun\n\nAV - Jambres 1; 1\n\nPretend to be sheltered = “a witch doctor who spits in his mouth”\n\n1) Yanni and Yanni were two Egyptian mages who imitated Aaron in front of the pharaoh\n The Miracle of the Way (#提后 3:8 |)',	1),
(5813,	'02403',	'2403 Iezabel {ee-ed-zab-ale\'}\n\n源自希伯来文0348; TDNT - 3:217,348; 阴性专有名词\n\nAV - Jezebel 1; 1\n\n耶洗别 = \"追赶\"\n\n1) 亚哈王的妻子, 是个残忍,不敬拜真神的王后,保护偶像崇拜,并迫害先知\n2) 一名妇女的象徵性名字.她自称为女先知,沉溺于唯信仰论(antinomianism),主张\n   基督徒可任意吃献给偶像的祭品 (#启 2:20|)',	'2403 Iezabel {ee-ed-zab-ale\'}\n\nFrom Hebrews 0348; TDNT - 3:217 ,348; proper noun for negativity\n\nAV - Jezebel 1; 1\n\nJezebel = “catch up”\n\n1) King Ahab\'s wife was a cruel queen who did not worship the true God, protected idolatry and persecuted the Prophet\n2) The symbolic name of a woman who calls herself a female prophet, indulges in antinomianism and advocates\n Christians are free to eat offerings dedicated to idols (#启 2:20 |)',	1),
(5814,	'02424',	'2424 Iesous {ee-ay-sooce\'}\n\n源自希伯来文 03091; TDNT - 3:284,360; 阳性专有名词\n\n钦定本 - Jesus 972, Jesus (Joshua) 2, Jesus (Justus) 1; 975\n\n耶稣 = 「耶和华是拯救」\n1) 耶稣, 上帝的儿子, 人类的救主, 上帝道成肉身\n2) 耶稣巴拉巴是被捕的强盗, 犹太人求彼拉多释放\n   巴拉巴, 而不是基督\n3) 约书亚是以色列人着名的领袖, 也是摩西的继承人\n   (#徒 7:45; 来 4:8|)\n4) 约细, 以利以谢的儿子, 基督的祖先 (#路 3:29|)\n5) 耶数, 姓犹士都, 为犹太裔基督徒, 是保罗传福音\n   的同工 (#西 4:11|)',	'2424 Iesous {ee-ay-sooce\'}\n\nFrom Hebrew 03091; TDNT - 3:284 ,360; positive proper noun\n\nThe definitive book - Jesus 972, Jesus (Joshua) 2, Jesus (Justus) 1; 975\n\njesus = “Jehovah is the salvation”\n1) Jesus, the Son of God, the Savior of mankind, God became flesh\n2) Jesus Barabbas was the arrested robber, and the Jews begged Pilate for release\n Barabbas, not Christ\n3) Joshua was a famous leader of the Israelites and heir to Moses\n (#徒 7:45; come 4:8 |)\n4) Jothi, son of Eli Eziah, ancestor of Christ (#路 3:29 |)\n5) Jesus, whose surname is Judas, is a Christian of Jewish descent, and is Paul who preached the gospel\n of coworkers (#西 4:11 |)',	1),
(5815,	'02459',	'2459 Ioustos {ee-ooce\'-tos}\n\n源自拉丁文 (\"公正的\"); 阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Justus (of Corinth) 1, Justus (surnamed Barabbas) 1,\n     Justus (Jesus, a fellow worker of Paul) 1; 3\n\n犹士都 = \"公正的\"\n1) 巴撒巴约瑟的另一名字 (#徒 1:23|)\n2) 提多犹士都:哥林多的一名信徒 (#徒 18:7|)\n3) 保罗的朋友耶数的名字 (#西 4:11|)',	'2459 Ioustos {ee-ooce\'-tos}\n\nDerived from Latin (“impartial”); proper noun for masculinity\n\nAV - Justus (of Corinth) 1, Justus (surnamed Barabbas) 1,\n Justus (Jesus, a fellow worker of Paul) 1; 3\n\njudas = “just”\n1) Another name for Joseph Bassaba (#徒 1:23 |)\n2) Titus Judas: A believer in Corinthians (#徒 18:7 |)\n3) The name of Paul\'s friend Jesus (#西 4:11 |)',	1),
(5816,	'02469',	'2469 Iskariotes {is-kar-ee-o\'-tace}\n\n可能源自希伯来文 0377 与 07149; 阳性专有名词\n\n钦定本 - Iscariot 11; 11\n\n加略 = \"加略人\"\n1) 耶稣的门徒犹大的姓氏',	'2469 Iskariotes {is-kar-ee-o\'-tace}\n\nPossibly derived from Hebrew 0377 vs 07149; positive proper noun\n\nConfinement Book - Iscariot 11; 11\n\nCallipsis = “Calyx people”\n1) The surname of Judas, a disciple of Jesus',	1),
(5817,	'02476',	'2476 histemi {his\'-tay-mee}\n\n基本字 stao (意思相同,只用在某些时态) 的扩张型; TDNT - 7:638,1082; 动词\n\nAV - stand 116, set 11, establish 5, stand still 4, stand by 3,\n     misc 17, vr stand 2; 158\n\n及物动词\n1) 放置, 带来, 容许前来\n2) 提出, 建议 (#徒 1:23|)\n3) 建立 (#罗 10:3; 来 10:9|)\n4) 保持, 使正更为确实, 确证 (#可 7:9; 罗 3:31|)\n5) 使站立 (#罗 14:4|)\n6) 定时间\n\n不及物, 过去不定, 未来式动词\n1) 停止, 站着不动\n2) 来到, 站出, 出现\n3) 抵抗 (#弗 6:11|)\n4) 坚定不移\n5) 站起来\n\n不及物, 完成式动词\n1) 站着\n2) 站在那里, 在那里\n3) 伺候 (#启 8:2|)\n4) 坚信不移\n5) 在某种状态里 (#约 8:44; 罗 5:2; 林前 15:1| )',	'2476 histemi {his\'-tay-mee}\n\nExpanded form of the basic word stao (same meaning, only used in certain tenses); TDNT - 7:638 ,1082; verb\n\nAV - stand 116, set 11, establish 5, stand still 4, stand by 3,\n misc 17, vr stand 2; 158\n\ntransitive verb\n1) Place, bring, allow to come\n2) Make suggestions (#徒 1:23 |)\n3) Build (#罗 10:3; come 10:9 |)\n4) Keep, make corrections more true, and confirmed (#可 7:9; Romans 3:31 |)\n5) Make it stand (#罗 14:4 |)\n6) Timed\n\nintransitive, past indefinite, futuristic verb\n1) Stop, stand still\n2) Come, Stand Out, Show Up\n3) Resistance (#弗 6:11 |)\n4) Unswerving\n5) Stand up\n\nintransitive, completed verb\n1) Standing\n2) Stand there, be there\n3) Servant (#启 8:2 |)\n4) Unswerving belief\n5) In a state (#约 8:44; Romans 5:2; Forests 15:1 |)',	1),
(5818,	'02479',	'2479 ischus {is-khoos\'}\n\n源自 is (力量, 参 eschon, 2192 之一型); TDNT - 3:397,378; 阴性名词\n\nAV - strength 4, power 2, might 2, ability 1, mightily + 1722 1,\n     mighty 1; 11\n\n1) 能力, 力量, 强壮程度, 力气\n\n其同义词, 见 5820',	'2479 ischus {is-khooos\'}\n\nDerived from is (power, ginseng eschon, type 2192); TDNT - 3:397 ,378; negative noun\n\nAV - strength 4, power 2, might 2, ability 1, mightily + 1722 1,\n mighty 1; 11\n\n1) Ability, strength, strength, strength\n\nFor synonyms, see 5820',	1),
(5819,	'02484',	'2484 Itouraia {ee-too-rah\'-yah}\n\n源自希伯来文03195; 形容词\n\nAV - Ituraea 1; 1\n\n以土利亚 = \"超越限制\" 或 \"他要安排\"\n1) 在巴勒斯坦东北部,大马色西边的山区.施洗约翰公开传道之际,\n   该区为分封王腓力管辖. 该区居民以抢劫与善用弓箭闻名 (#路 3:1|)',	'2484 Itouraia {ee-too-rah\'-yah}\n\nFrom Hebrew 03195; adjective\n\nAV - Ituraea 1; 1\n\nEtoria = “beyond the limit” or “he wants to arrange”\n1) On the occasion of the public preaching of John the Baptist in the mountains west of Damascus, in north-eastern Palestine,\n The district was under the jurisdiction of King Philip. Residents of the district are known for robberies and good use of bows and arrows (#路 3:1 |)',	1),
(5820,	'03007',	'3007 leipo {li\'-po}\n\n字根字; 动词\n\nAV - lack 2, be wanting 2, want + 1722 1, be destitute 1; 6\n\n1) 留下, 遗留\n   1a) 劣于, 不够标准, 缺少 (#雅 1:4|)\n   1b) 需要, 缺乏 (#雅 1:15; 2:15|)\n2) 欠缺, 缺少(一些必要的东西) (#路 18:22; 多 1:5; 3:13|)',	'3007 leipo {li\'-po}\n\nroot word; verb\n\nAV - lack 2, be deformed 2, want + 1722 1, be deformed 1; 6\n\n1) left behind, left behind\n 1a) inferior, substandard, missing (#雅 1:4 |)\n 1b) Needs, Lack (#雅 1:15; 2:15 |)\n2) Deficient, lacking (something necessary) (#路 18:22; more 1:5; 3:13 |)',	1),
(5821,	'02305',	'2305 theiotes {thi-ot\'-ace}\n\n源自 2304; TDNT - 3:123,322; 阴性名词\n\nAV - Godhead 1; 1\n\n1) 神性, 神性的本质(#罗 1:20|)\n\n同义词 见 5849',	'2305 theiotes {thi-ot\'-ace}\n\nDerived from 2304; TDNT - 3:123 ,322; negative noun\n\nAV - Godhead 1; 1\n\n1) Divinity, the essence of divinity (#罗 1:20 |)\n\nSee 5849 for synonyms',	1),
(5822,	'02309',	'2309 thelo {thel\'-o} 或 ethelo {eth-el\'-o} (在某些时态中用)\n     theleo {thel-eh\'-o} 和 etheleo {eth-el-eh\'-o} 已不再使用\n     \n显然是 138 的替代字的加强型; TDNT - 3:44,318; 动词\n\nAV - will/would 159, will/would have 16, desire 13, desirous 3,\n     list 3, to will 2, misc 4; 210\n\n1) 愿意, 有意思要..., 想要拥有\n2) 决定, 意欲, 准备好\n3) 喜欢\n4) 主张 (#彼后 3:5|)',	'2309 thelo {thel\'-o} or ethelo {eth-el\'-o} (used in some tenses)\n Theleo {thel-eh\'-o} and etheleo {eth-el-eh\'-o} are no longer in use\n \nApparently the reinforcement of the alternative word 138; TDNT - 3:44 ,318; verb\n\nAV - will/would 159, will/would have 16, desire 13, desirable 3,\n list 3, to will 2, misc 4; 210\n\n1) Willing, interesting to..., want to have\n2) Decide, Willingness, and Readiness\n3) Like\n4) Advocate (#彼后 3:5 |)',	1),
(5823,	'02364',	'2364 thugater {thoo-gat\'-air}\n\n显然是一个字根字; 阴性名词\n\nAV - daughter 29; 29\n\n1)女儿\n  1a) 亲生女儿\n  1b) 视为自己的女儿\n  1c) 祖先,政治群体或某个阶层中的女性\n  1d) 拟人化为女儿 #太 21:5; 约 12:15|',	'2364 thugater {thoo-gat\'-air}\n\nApparently a root word; a negative noun\n\nAV - daughter 29; 29\n\n1) Daughter\n 1a) biological daughter\n 1b) Treat yourself as your daughter\n 1c) Women in ancestry, political group, or class\n 1d) Personified as daughter #太 21:5; approx. 12:15 |',	1),
(5824,	'02370',	'2370 thumiao {thoo-mee-ah\'-o}\n\n源自 2380 的衍生字 (取其冒烟之意); 动词\n\nAV - burn incense 1; 1\n\n1) 烧香 (#路1;9|)',	'2370 thumiao {thoo-mee-ah\'-o}\n\nDerivative word from 2380 (meaning smoke); verb\n\nAV - burn incense 1; 1\n\n1) Burning incense (#路1; 9|)',	1),
(5825,	'02266',	'2266 Herodias {hay-ro-dee-as\'}\n\n源自 2264; 阴性专有名词\n\n钦定本 - Herodias 6; 6\n\n希罗底 = \"英勇的\"\n1)亚利多布的女儿、大希律的孙女.先是嫁给希律腓力一世, \n  大希律的儿子 ;后来跟希律安提帕有不合法的关系, 并诱\n  使希律安提帕杀害施洗约翰 ，不过罗马之行也毁了希律\n  安提帕;最后两人被放逐于高卢.',	'2266 Herodias {hay-ro-dee-as\'}\n\nDerived from 2264; proper noun for negativity\n\nAdmiration Book - Herodias 6; 6\n\nherodes = “heroic”\n1) The daughter of Aridob, the granddaughter of Herod the Great. She first married Herod Philip I. \n son of the elder Herod; later had an illegal relationship with Herod Antipas, and seduced\n Caused Herod Antipa to kill John the Baptist, but the trip to Rome also ruined Herod\n Antipa; the last two were exiled to Gaul.',	1),
(5826,	'02549',	'2549 kakia {kak-ee\'-ah}\n\n源自 2556; TDNT - 3:482,391; 阴性名词\n\nAV - malice 6, maliciousness 2, evil 1, wickedness 1, naughtiness 1; 11\n\n1) 恶念, 歹意\n2) 邪恶, 卑劣\n3) 厄运, 难关 (#太 6:34|)\n\n同义词 见 5855',	'2549 kakia {kak-ee\'-ah}\n\nDerived from 2556; TDNT - 3:482 ,391; negative noun\n\nAV - Malice 6, Maliciousness 2, Evil 1, Wickedness 1, Naughtiness 1; 11\n\n1) Disgust, malice\n2) Wicked, vile\n3) Doom, Difficulty (#太 6:34 |)\n\nSee 5855 for synonyms',	1),
(5827,	'02581',	'2581 Kananites {kan-an-ee\'-tace}\n\n源自亚兰文, 参 07067; 阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Canaanite 2; 2\n\n1) 原意为\"热心,狂热\",在新约用来称呼耶稣的门徒西门,因为他以前可能隶属\"激进\"或\"自由战士\"党派\n   因此和合本译为\"奋锐党的\" (#太 10:4; 可 3:18|)',	'2581 Kananites {kan-an-ee\'-tace}\n\nDerived from Aramaic, ginseng 07067; positive proper noun\n\nAV - Canaanite 2; 2\n\n1) Originally meant “zealous, fanatical”, used in the New Testament to refer to Jesus\' disciple Simon, as he may have previously belonged to the “radical” or “freedom fighter” parties\n Therefore, the sum is translated as “Enrui Party\'s” (#太 10:4; May 3:18 |)',	1),
(5828,	'02588',	'2588 kardia {kar-dee\'-ah}\n\n基本字 kar (拉丁文, cor, \"心\") 的扩充型; TDNT - 3:605,415; 阴性名词\n\n钦定本- heart 159, broken hearted + 4937 1; 160\n\n1) 心\n 1a) 动物身体的器官;血液循环的中心, 因此被看做\n       是物质肉体生命的活动中心位置。\n 1b) 内在命的中心与源头。\n  1b1) 神与基督对人类内在生命的全然感知\n  1b2) 内在的感知\n  1b3) 意志与决心\n  1b4) 道德生命的决定\n  1b5) 情感, 愿望, 渴望\n  1b6) 爱\n  1b7) 性情\n  1b8) 神以及他的能力居留之处 ',	'2588 kardia {kar-dee\'-ah}\n\nExpanded form of the basic word kar (Latin, cor, “heart”); TDNT - 3:605 ,415; negative noun\n\nChinding book - heart 159, broken hearted + 4937 1; 160\n\n1) Heart\n 1a) an organ of the animal\'s body; the center of blood circulation, and is therefore regarded as\n It is the center of activity of material physical life.\n 1b) The center and source of inner life.\n 1b1) God and Christ\'s total perception of human life\n 1b2) Intrinsic perception\n 1b3) Will and determination\n 1b4) Decisions on Moral Life\n 1b5) Emotions, Wishes, Desires\n 1b6) Love\n 1b7) Temperament\n 1b8) Where God and His Abilities Dwell',	1),
(5829,	'02647',	'2647 kataluo {kat-al-oo\'-o}\n\n源自 2596 and 3089; TDNT - 4:338,543; 动词\n\nAV - destroy 9, throw down 3, lodge 1, guest 1, come to nought 1,\n     overthrow 1, dissolve 1; 17\n\n1) (从建筑物)拆下,拿开(石头)\n2) 毁坏,拆毁,拆散\n 2a)建筑物\n 2b)喻意\n3) 终止\n 3a)废弃,使之无效\n 3b)破坏 (#徒 5:38,39|)\n4) 中止(正在做的事)(字意为\"卸下动物的缰\"),休息,投宿 (#太 6:28|)\n   ',	'2647 kataluo {kat-al-oo\'-o}\n\nFrom 2596 and 3089; TDNT - 4:338 ,543; verb\n\nAV - destroy 9, throw down 3, lodge 1, guest 1, come to nought 1,\n overthrow 1, dissolve 1; 17\n\n1) Remove (from building), take away (stone)\n2) Destruction, demolition, dismantling\n 2a) Buildings\n 2b) Yu Yi\n3) Termination\n 3a) Abandoned, making it null and void\n 3b) Destruction (#徒 5:38 ,39|)\n4) Stop (what is being done) (the word means “remove the stern of the animal”), rest, lodging (#太 6:28 |)',	1),
(5830,	'02665',	'2665 katapetasma {kat-ap-et\'-as-mah}\n\n源于 2596 的复合字和 4072 的同类词; TDNT - 3:628,420; 中性名词\n\nAV - veil 6; 6\n\n1) 幔子\n   1a) 这个名词用来指在耶路撒冷圣殿中的两个幔子, 一个是分开圣所和外院的, 另一个\n       则是将至圣所和圣所分别开来',	'2665 katapetasma {kat-ap-et\'-as-mah}\n\nCompound words derived from 2596 and equivalent words from 4072; TDNT - 3:628 ,420; neutral nouns\n\nAV - veil 6; 6\n\n1) Mantle\n 1a) The term is used to refer to the two mantles in the Temple of Jerusalem, one separating the Sanctuary from the Outer Court and the other\n Separate the Sanctuary from the Sanctuary',	1),
(5831,	'02716',	'2716 katergazomai {kat-er-gad\'-zom-ahee}\n\n源自 2596 与 2038; TDNT - 3:634,421; 动词\n\nAV - work 15, do 5, do deed 1, to perform 1, cause 1, work out 1; 24\n\n1) 达成, 完成, 做\n2) 致使, 产生, 创造\n3) 使准备周全 (#林后 5:5|)\n4) 克服, 制服, 征服 (#弗 6:13|)',	'2716 katergazomai {kat-er-gad\'-zom-ahee}\n\nDerived from 2596 vs 2038; TDNT - 3:634 ,421; verb\n\nAV - work 15, do 5, do perform 1, to perform 1, cause 1, work out 1; 24\n\n1) Achieve, Complete, Do\n2) cause, produce, create\n3) Be well prepared (#林后 5:5 |)\n4) Overcome, Conquer, Conquer (#弗 6:13 |)',	1),
(5832,	'02722',	'2722 katecho {kat-ekh\'-o}\n\n源于 2596 与 2192; TDNT - 2:829,286; 动词\n\nAV - hold 3, hold fast 3, keep 2, possess 2, stay 1, take 1, have 1,\n     make 1, misc 5; 19\n\n1) 防止, 阻碍, 压制\n2) 坚守, 坚信\n3) 拥有\n4) 占有 (#路 14:9|)\n5) 提出所有权 (#罗 1:18|)\n6) 航向 (#徒 27:40|)\n   ',	'2722 katecho {kat-ekh\'-o}\n\nfrom 2596 vs 2192; TDNT - 2:829 ,286; verb\n\nAV - hold 3, hold fast 3, keep 2, stay 1, take 1, have 1,\n make 1, misc 5; 19\n\n1) Preventing, hindering, suppressing\n2) Stick to it, firmly believe\n3) Possession\n4) Possession (#路 14:9 |)\n5) Propose Ownership (#罗 1:18 |)\n6) Course (#徒 27:40 |)',	1),
(5833,	'02752',	'2752 keleuma {kel\'-yoo-mah}\n\n源于 2753; TDNT - 3:656,*; 中性名词\n\nAV - shout 1; 1\n\n1) 一个指令, 命令, 更确定地说, 指以一种吼叫, 呼喊的方式所发出, 以催逼采取行动的. \n   不论是动物被人叫唤驱策, 如马被驾战车的士兵催促, 猎犬被猎人呼叫等等; 或是给与人的\n   一个信号, 如船主给划船手的口令, 指挥官对士兵下达的命令(以口令或号角传达)等等 (#帖前 4:16|)',	'2752 keleuma {kel\'-yoo-mah}\n\nDerived from 2753; TDNT - 3:656, *; neutral noun\n\nAV - shout 1; 1\n\n1) An instruction, order, or more specifically, is issued in a manner of yelling or shouting in order to induce action. \n Whether animals are called to be driven by people, such as horses being urged by soldiers driving chariots, hounds being called by hunters, etc.; or for people\n A signal, such as the owner\'s password to the rower, the commander\'s order to the soldier (communicated by password or horn), etc. (#帖前 4:16 |)',	1),
(5834,	'02790',	'2790 kitharodos {kith-ar-o\'-dos}\n\n源自 2788 以及与5603同源的衍生字; 阳性名词\n\nAV - harper 2; 2\n\n1) 竖琴乐手 (#启 14:2, 18:22|)',	'2790 kitharodos {kith-ar-o\'-dos}\n\nDerived from 2788 and derivative words homologous to 5603; masculine noun\n\nAV - harper 2; 2\n\n1) Harp musicians (#启 14:2, 18:22 |)',	1),
(5835,	'02804',	'2804 Klaudios {klow\'-dee-os}\n\n源自拉丁文; 阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Claudius (Caesar) 2, Claudius (Lysias) 1; 3\n\n革老丢 = \"残废的\"\n1) 罗马第四任皇帝,主后41年登基,最后被妻子毒死 (#徒 11:28,18:2|)\n2) 耶路撒冷的一名罗马官员 (#徒 23:26|)',	'2804 Klaudios {klow\'-dee-os}\n\nDerived from Latin; proper noun for masculinity\n\nAV - Claudius (Caesar) 2, Claudius (Lysias) 1; 3\n\nLost in old age = “crippled”\n1) The fourth emperor of Rome, came to the throne in 41 and was finally poisoned by his wife (#徒 11:28, 18:2 |)\n2) A Roman official in Jerusalem (#徒 23:26 |)',	1),
(5836,	'02873',	'2873 kopos {kop\'-os}\n\n源自2875; TDNT - 3:827,453;阳性名词\n\nAV - labour 13, trouble + 3830 5, weariness 1; 19\n\n1) 困难, 烦恼\n2) 工作, 劳力\n\n同义词见 5860',	'2873 kopos {kop\'-os}\n\nDerived from 2875; TDNT - 3:827,453; positive noun\n\nAV - labor 13, trouble + 3830 5, weariness 1; 19\n\n1) Difficulties, troubles\n2) Work, labor\n\nSee 5860 for synonyms',	1),
(5837,	'02878',	'2878 korban {kor-ban\'} and korbanas {kor-ban-as\'}\n\n源自希伯来文与亚兰文, 参 07133; TDNT - 3:860,459; 阳性名词\n\nAV - treasury 1, corban 1; 2\n\n1) 献给神的祭物, 各耳板 (#太 27:6; 可 7:11|)',	'2878 korban {kor-ban\'} and korbanas {kor-ban-as\'}\n\nFrom Hebrew and Aramaic, cf. 07133; TDNT - 3:860,459; masculine noun\n\nAV - treasury 1, corban 1; 2\n\n1) A sacrifice to God, each ear plate (#太 27:6; May 7:11 |)',	1),
(5838,	'03454',	'3454 muthos {moo\'-thos}\n\n可能与3453同源 (取其传授之意); TDNT - 4:762,610;阳性名词\n\nAV - fable 5; 5\n\n1) 故事, 传奇, 神话',	'3454 muthos {moo\'-thos}\n\nMay be homologous to 3453 (as taught); TDNT - 4:762 ,610; masculine noun\n\nAV - fable 5; 5\n\n1) Story, Legend, Myth',	1),
(5839,	'02502',	'2502 Iosias {ee-o-see\'-as}\n\n源自希伯来文 02977; 阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Josias 2; 2\n\n约西亚= \"耶和华所医治的\"\n1) 犹大王, 在犹太人中恢复真神的敬拜, 统治31年, 约主前611年, 死于战场 (#太 1:10-11|)',	'2502 Iosias {ee-o-see\'-as}\n\nFrom Hebrew 02977; proper noun for masculinity\n\nAV - Josias 2; 2\n\nJosiah = “Healed by Jehovah”\n1) King of Judah, who restored the worship of God among the Jews, ruled for 31 years, 611 years before John, and died on the battlefield (#太 1:10-11 |)',	1),
(5840,	'02504',	'2504 kago {kag-o\'}\n\n源自 2532 与 1473 (kamoi {kam-oy\'} 的与格, \n以及 kame {kam-eh\'} 的宾格); 连接词\n\nAV - and I 34, I also 17, so I 4, I 4, even I 3, me also 3, misc 7; 72\n\n1) 和我\n2) 而我\n3) 我也\n4) 尤其是我 (#罗 3:7|)\n5) 若我 (太 26:15|)',	'2504 kago {kag-o\'}\n\nFrom the datum of 2532 and 1473 (kamoi {kam-oy\'}, \nand the accusative case of kame {kam-eh\'}); conjunction\n\nAV - and I 34, I also 17, so I 4, I 4, even I 3, me also 3, misc 7; 72\n\n1) With me\n2) And I\n3) I too\n4) Especially Me (#罗 3:7 |)\n5) If I (Too 26:15 |)',	1),
(5841,	'02542',	'2542 Kaisereia {kahee-sar\'-i-a}\n\n源自 2541; 专有地名\n\nAV - Caesarea (of Palestine) 15, Caesarea (Philippi) 2; 17\n\n该撒利亚 = \"切断的\"\n1) 位于黑门山脚下的一座城,原先称为Paneas;后来由分封王腓立比重建,\n   起名为该撒利亚,纪念该撒提比留斯(Tiberias Caesar) (#太16:13; 可 8:27|)\n2) 位于迦密山南方的城市,由希律大帝所建,纪念该撒奥古斯督,后来成为\n   罗马总督所在地.',	'2542 Kaisereia {kahee-sar\'-i-a}\n\nDerived from 2541; proprietary place name\n\nAV - Caesarea (of Palestine) 15, Caesarea (Philippi) 2; 17\n\nthe thaliah = “severed”\n1) A city located at the foot of Mount Hermon, originally known as Paneas; it was later rebuilt by King Philippians,\n Named Caesaria, in honor of Tiberias Caesar (#太16:13; May 8:27 |)\n2) A city located south of Mount Carmine, built by Herod the Great, in honor of Augustus Caesar, which later became\n The seat of the Governor of Rome.',	1),
(5842,	'03094',	'3094 Magdalene {mag-dal-ay-nay\'}\n\n源自 3093 的衍生字; 阴性专有名词\n\nAV - Magdalene 12; 12\n\n抹大拉= \"高塔\"\n1) 用来称呼来自抹大拉的马利亚',	'3094 Magdalene {mag-dal-ay-nay\'}\n\nDerived from 3093; proper noun for negativity\n\nAV - Magdalene 12; 12\n\nMagdalene = “high tower”\n1) Used to call Mary from Magdalene',	1),
(5843,	'03104',	'3104 Mainan {mahee-nan\'}\n\n可能源自希伯来文; 阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Menan 1; 1\n\n买南= \"预言者: 着魔的\"\n1) 在耶稣基督族谱中, 约瑟的一位组先 (#路 3:31|)',	'3104 Mainan {mahee-nan\'}\n\nPossibly derived from Hebrew; proper noun for masculinity\n\nAV - Menan 1; 1\n\nBuy Nan = “Prophet: Enchanted”\n1) In the genealogy of Jesus Christ, one of Joseph\'s groups comes first (#路 3:31 |)',	1),
(5844,	'03137',	'3137 Maria {mar-ee\'-ah} 或 Mariam {mar-ee-am\'}\n\n源于希伯来文 04813; 阴性专有名词 人名\n\nAV - Mary the mother of Jesus 19, Mary Magdalene 13,\n     Mary the sister of Martha 11, Mary the mother of James 9,\n     Mary the mother of John Mark 1, Mary of Rome 1; 54\n\n马利亚 \n1) 耶稣的母亲马利亚\n2) 抹大拉的马利亚\n3) 拉撒路和马大的姐妹马利亚\n4) 革罗罢的妻子马利亚, 是雅各及约西的母亲 (#约 19:25;太 27:56;可 15:40-41; 16:1;路 24:10|)\n5) 约翰马可的母亲马利亚, 巴拿巴的姐妹(#徒 12:12|)\n6) 一位罗马的基督徒马利亚, 保罗在#罗 16:6|曾特别问她的安',	'3137 Maria {mar-ee\'-ah} or Mariam {mar-ee-am\'}\n\nDerived from Hebrew 04813; proper noun name for negative\n\nAV - Mary the mother of Jesus 19, Mary Magdalene 13,\n Mary the sister of Martha 11, Mary the mother of James 9,\n Mary the mother of John Mark 1, Mary of Rome 1; 54\n\nMaria \n1) Mary, the mother of Jesus\n2) Mary Magdalene\n3) Lazarus and Ma Tai\'s sister Maria\n4) Mary, Grotten\'s wife, was the mother of Jacob and Joses (#约 19:25; Matthew 27:56; May 15:40-41; 16:1; Luke 24:10 |)\n5) John Marco\'s mother Maria, sister of Barnabas (#徒 12:12 |)\n6) A Roman Christian Mary, Paul specifically asked her Ann at #罗 16:6',	1),
(5845,	'03138',	'3138 Markos {mar\'-kos}\n\n源于拉丁文; 阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Mark 5, Marcus 3; 8\n\n马可 = \"答辩\"\n1) 一位宣道者, 马可福音的作者, \"马可\"是他的拉丁文的姓, 约翰是他的犹太名字. \n   他是巴拿巴的表亲, 他曾伴随保罗在其部分的传教旅程中',	'3138 Markos {mar\'-kos}\n\nDerived from Latin; proper noun for masculinity\n\nAV - Mark 5, Marcus 3; 8\n\nmarco = “reply”\n1) A preacher, author of the Gospel of Mark, “Mark” is his Latin surname, and John is his Jewish name. \n He was a cousin of Barnabas, and he had accompanied Paul on part of his missionary journey',	1),
(5846,	'03140',	'3140 martureo {mar-too-reh\'-o}\n\n源于 3144; TDNT - 4:474,564; 动词\n\nAV - bear witness 25, testify 19, bear record 13, witness 5,\n     be a witness 2, give testimony 2, have a good report 2, misc 11; 79\n\n1) 作证, 成为证人\n2) 美言, 赞许, 作有利证词',	'3140 martureo {mar-too-reh\'-o}\n\nfrom 3144; TDNT - 4:474 ,564; verb\n\nAV - bear witness 25, testify 19, bear record 13, witness 5,\n Be a witness 2, give witness 2, have a good report 2, misc 11; 79\n\n1) Testify and be a witness\n2) Good words, praise, and favorable testimony',	1),
(5847,	'03173',	'3173 megas {meg\'-as}\n\n[包括扩张型, 阴性 megale, 复数 megaloi 等, 亦参 03176, 03187]; TDNT - 4:529,573; 形容词\n\n钦定本 - great 150, loud 33, misc 12; 195\n\n1) 大\n   1a) 向四方扩展的空间\n   1b) 宽敞\n   1c) 数字\n   1d) 年纪\n2) (量方面超出一般) 多 (#提前 6:6; 来 10:35|)\n3) (程度上超出一般) 大 (特别是声音)\n4) (更为重要) 伟大, 宏伟\n   4a) 神\n   4b) 事物\n5) (不寻常) 意外, 令人惊奇的 (#林前 9:11; 林后 11:15|)',	'3173 megas {meg\'-as}\n\n[including dilated, negative megale, plural megaloi, etc., see also 03176, 03187]; TDNT - 4:529 ,573; adjectives\n\nChinding book - great 150, loud 33, misc 12; 195\n\n1) large\n 1a) Space to expand to the Quartet\n 1b) roomy\n 1c) Numbers\n 1d) age\n2) More (more than average in terms of volume) (#提前 6:6; to 10:35 |)\n3) Loud (more than average) (especially sound)\n4) (More Important) Great, Magnificent\n 4a) God\n 4b) Things\n5) (Unusual) Unexpected, Amazing (#林前 9:11; After Forest 11:15 |)',	1),
