(5878,	'03970',	'3970 patroparadotos {pat-rop-ar-ad\'-ot-os}\n\n源自 3962 与 3860 的衍生字 (取其交给或留下来的意思); 形容词\n\nAV - received by tradition from (one\'s) fathers 1; 1\n\n1) 从祖先或父家传承下来的 (#彼前 1:18|)',	'3970 patroparadotos {pat-rop-ar-ad\'-ot-os}\n\nDerivative words from 3962 and 3860 (meaning to give or stay); adjectives\n\nAV - received by tradition from (one\'s) 1; 1\n\n1) Passed down from ancestors or fathers (#彼前 1:18 |)',	1),
(5879,	'03972',	'3972 Paulos {pow\'-los}\n\n源自拉丁文; 阳性专有名词\n\n钦定本 - Paul 163, Paulus (the deputy) 1; 164\n\n保罗 = 「小的或少的」\n\n1) 保罗是有名的使徒之一, 写了十三卷保罗书信.\n\n2) 士求保罗是居比路 (塞浦路斯) 的方伯 (即省长) , 听说为人精明\n   (#徒 13:7|)',	'3972 Paulos {pow\'-los}\n\nDerived from Latin; proper noun for masculinity\n\nThe definitive book - Paul 163, Paulus (the founder) 1; 164\n\npaul = “small or less”\n\n1) Paul was one of the famous apostles, who wrote thirteen volumes of the Epistle to Paul.\n\n2) ShikubPaul is a square (i.e. governor) of Gubilo (Cyprus), heard to be a savvy person\n (#徒 13:7 |)',	1),
(5880,	'03982',	'3982 peitho {pi\'-tho}\n\n原型动词; TDNT - 6:1,818; 动词\n\nAV - persuade 22, trust 8, obey 7, have confidence 6, believe 3,\n     be confident 2, misc 7; 55\n\n1) 使之接受某观点或采取行动 \n  1a) 说服\n  1b) 劝说, 诉求, (或是负面的) 误导, 诱使\n  1c) 赢得, 取悦 (#徒 12:20;14:19; 加 1:10|)\n  1d) 平息, 安歇 (#太 28:14; 约壹 3:19|)\n2) 被说服进而信任\n  2a) 倚靠, 信赖\n  2b) 被说服, 确定\n3) 藉着劝说赢得\n  3a) 被说服, 相信\n  3b) 顺服, 跟从\n4) (被动式) 对某件事得到确认\n  4a) 确信, 确定',	'3982 peitho {pi\'-tho}\n\narchetypal verb; TDNT - 6:1 ,818; verb\n\nAV - persuade 22, trust 8, obey 7, have confidence 6, believe 3,\n be 2, misc 7; 55\n\n1) Make them accept a point of view or take action \n 1a) Persuade\n 1b) Persuade, appeal, (or negatively) mislead, induce\n 1c) Win, Pleasure (#徒 12:20; 14:19; plus 1:10 |)\n 1d) Calm down, rest (#太 28:14; approx. 3:19 |)\n2) Be persuaded and then trusted\n 2a) Relying on, trusting\n 2b) Be persuaded, OK\n3) Win by persuasion\n 3a) Be persuaded, believe\n 3b) Obey, obey\n4) Get confirmation of something (passive)\n 4a) Be sure, be sure',	1),
(5881,	'04005',	'4005 pentekoste {pen-tay-kos-tay\'}\n\n4004 序数的阴性; TDNT - 6:44,826; 阴性名词\n\n钦定本 - Pentecost 3; 3\n\n五旬节 = 「第五十天」\n1) 三大犹太节期中第二大节期, 每年于耶路撒冷庆祝\n   时间是逾越节后第七个礼拜, 表彰收获完成的感恩',	'4005 pentekoste {pen-tay-kos-tay\'}\n\n4004 Ordinal Negative; TDNT - 6:44 ,826; Negative Noun\n\nThe definitive book - Pentecost 3; 3\n\npentecost = “day 50”\n1) The second largest of the three major Jewish festivals, celebrated every year in Jerusalem\n The time is the seventh week after Passover, in recognition of the thanksgiving for the completion of the harvest',	1),
