(5884,	'04050',	'4050 perisseia {per-is-si\'-ah}\n\n源自 4052; TDNT - 6:63,828; 阴性名词\n\n钦定本 - abundance 2, abundantly 1, superfluity 1; 4\n\n1) 丰富, 大量地, 过分地 (#罗 5:17; 林后 8:2|)\n2) 增加, 利益 (#林后 10:15|)\n3) 剩余, 遗迹: 基督徒信主以前心里残余留下的恶 (#雅 1:21|)',	'4050 perisseia {per-is-si\'-ah}\n\nFrom 4052; TDNT - 6:63 ,828; negative noun\n\nChing Book - Abundantly 2, Abundantly 1, Superfluity 1; 4\n\n1) Abundant, Massively, Excessively (#罗 5:17; After Forest 8:2 |)\n2) Increase, Benefit (#林后 10:15 |)\n3) Remnant, Remains: The Remnant Evil Left in the Heart of Christians Before Believers (#雅 1:21 |)',	1),
(5885,	'04067',	'4067 peripsema {per-ip\'-say-mah}\n\n源自4012的比较级与 psao (擦拭); TDNT - 6:84,*; 中性名词\n\nAV - offscouring 1; 1\n\n1) 尘土, 渣滓 (#林前 4:13|)\n\n雅典人为了防止浩劫,每年将一个囚犯丢入海里献给海神.该名词用来指代赎的祭物,赎价.\n亦即为了救自己儿子的生命,让这个人的生命成为受人唾弃,没有价值的生命,以用来作为\n替别人死的祭物.\n\n',	'4067 peripsema {per-ip\'-say-mah}\n\nComparative rank from 4012 with psao (wipe); TDNT - 6:84, *; neutral noun\n\nAV - offscouring1; 1\n\n1) Dust, Dregs (#林前 4:13 |)\n\nIn order to prevent havoc, the Athenians threw one prisoner into the sea every year to offer to the god of the sea. The term was used to refer to a ransom sacrifice, a ransom.\nIn other words, in order to save the life of one\'s own son, let this person\'s life become a life that is rejected and worthless, and used as a\nA sacrifice to die for someone else.',	1),
(5886,	'04083',	'4083 pechus {pay\'-khoos}\n\n字源不详; 阳性名词\n\nAV - cubit 4; 4\n\n1) 一腕尺\n2) 长度的度量, 相当于自肘到中指之间连结的距离 (亦即大约18寸,\n   (.5 公尺)  但它的精确长度会改变且有争议',	'4083 pechus {pay\'-khoos}\n\nUnknown origin; masculine noun\n\nAV - cubit 4; 4\n\n1) One wrist\n2) The measurement of length, equivalent to the distance between the elbow and the middle finger (ie about 18 inches,\n (.5 meters) but its exact length varies and is controversial',	1),
(5887,	'04314',	'4314 pros {pros}\n\n4253 的加强型; TDNT - 6:720,942; 介系词\n\nAV - unto 340, to 203, with 43, for 25, against 24, among 20, at 11,\n     not tr 6, misc 53, vr to 1; 726\n\n1) 有...的优势 (#徒 27:34|)\n2) 在..., 近..., 靠...之处\n3) 时间与方向的移动\n 3a) 去..., 朝向...\n 3b) (时间) 将近, 某段时间的当中\n 3c) (目标) 朝向, 对准\n 3d) (关系) 赞许, 反对\n 3e) 有关\n 3f) 在(某人)一旁',	'4314 pros {pros}\n\n4253 fortified; TDNT - 6:720 ,942; mesons\n\nAV - unto 340, to 203, with 43, for 25, against 24, among 20, at 11,\n not tr 6, misc 53, vr to 1; 726\n\n1) Have the advantage of... (#徒 27:34 |)\n2) In..., near..., by...\n3) Movement in time and direction\n 3a) Go..., towards...\n 3b) (time) is approaching, in a certain period of time\n 3c) (target) towards, alignment\n 3d) (relationship) praise, disagree\n 3e) Related\n 3f) Beside (someone)',	1),
(5888,	'04160',	'4160 poieo {poy-eh\'-o}\n\n显然是一个不使用的原形字的扩张型; TDNT - 6:458,895; 动词\n\nAV - do 357, make 113, bring forth 14, commit 9, cause 9, work 8,\n     show 5, bear 4, keep 4, fulfil 3, deal 2, perform 2, not tr 3,\n     misc 43, vr do 3; 579\n\n1) 制造, 产生\n  1a) 人的行动\n  1b) 神的作为\n2) 作, 带出, 实现, 完成, 准备\n  2a) 行事\n  2b) 施行 (神迹) \n  2c) 建立, 形成某种状态\n  2d) 准备筵席,或是节日\n  2e) (自然生长过程) 发出, 产生, 生长\n  2f) 致使, 带出某中结果\n3) 作, 遵行, 履行, 练习, 犯下\n  3a) 遵行旨意与律法\n  3b) 实行, 操练美德\n  3c) 犯罪作恶\n  3d) 行善, 作得好\n  3e) 照着去作\n4) 对人或物作出某事\n  4a) 与某人一起作某事\n  4b) 对人有利\n  4c) 对人不利\n  4d) 照样对待\n5) 活动, 活跃于\n6) 为自己作某事或作成某物\n       \n同义词见5871',	'4160 poieo {poy-eh\'-o}\n\nApparently an expanded form of an unused prototype; TDNT - 6:458 ,895; verb\n\nAV - do 357, make 113, bring forth 14, commit 9, cause 9, work 8,\n show 5, bear 4, keep 4, deal 3, deal 2, perform 2, not tr 3,\n misc 43, vr do 3; 579\n\n1) Manufacture, production\n 1a) Human actions\n 1b) Acts of God\n2) Make, bring out, achieve, complete, prepare\n 2a) Act\n 2b) Enforcement (Miracle) \n 2c) establish, form a certain state\n 2d) Prepare for a feast, or a festival\n 2e) (natural growth process) emit, produce, grow\n 2f) Causes, brings out the result of a certain\n3) Make, obey, perform, practice, commit\n 3a) Obeying the Will and the Law\n 3b) Practice, practice virtues\n 3c) Criminal mischief\n 3d) Do good, do well\n 3e) Follow\n4) Do something to a person or thing\n 4a) Do something with someone\n 4b) Good for people\n 4c) Bad for people\n 4d) Treat\n5) Be active, active\n6) Do something for yourself or make something\n \nSee 5871 for synonyms',	1),
(5889,	'04183',	'4183 polus {pol-oos\'}, pollei, polu\n\n包括 pollos 的替代型; TDNT - 6:536,*; 形容词\n\nAV - many 210, much 73, great 59, misc 23; 365\n\n1) 为数众多的, 相当分量的, 大量的\n 1a) 数目上的\n 1b) 数量上的\n 1c) 程度上的\n\n另参简明希汉字典字义:\n(1)所有格 pollou, polleis, pollou:\n   多(大[群人]; [号啕]大[哭]; 丰[收]; 深[土]; [天]很晚; 多[年];\n(2)polla:\n    多东西, 许多事; 副词: 屡次;严厉地; 坚持地; 强烈地; \n    辛勤地;衷心地; 热切地;\n   polu:\n    多, 非常, 大大地\n   polu mallon\n    更加, 更为 (来十二9, 25)\n   pollw mollon\n    更加; 更为\n   pollw pleious\n    更多 (约四41)\n   pollou\n    庞大的数目 (太二十六9)',	'4183 polus {pol-oos\'}, pollei, polu\n\nAlternatives to include pollos; TDNT - 6:536, *; adjectives\n\nAV - many 210, much 73, great 59, misc 23; 365\n\n1) A large number of, considerable weight, a large number of\n 1a) numerical\n 1b) Quantitative\n 1c) degree\n\nSee also the meaning of the concise Greek Chinese dictionary:\n(1) Possessive pollou, polleis, pollou:\n Many (big [group of people]; [number] big [cry]; abundance [harvest]; deep [soil]; [day] very late; many [years];\n(2) Polla:\n many things, many things; adverb: repeatedly; harshly; persistently; strongly; \n hard work; heartily; eagerly;\n polu:\n much, very, greatly\n polu mallon\n More, more (to twelve 9, 25)\n pollw mollon\n more; more\n pollw pleious\n More (about 441)\n Pollou\n A huge number (too twenty-six nine)',	1),
