(5902,	'04982',	'4982 sozo {sode\'-zo}\n\n源于一字根型的 sos (一已不用的字 saoz 的缩写, 意为\"安全的\");\n   TDNT - 7:965,1132; 动词\nAV - save 93, make whole 9, heal 3, be whole 2, misc 3; 110\n\n1) 救助, 保全, 由危险和自然灾害中拯救出来\n 1a) 免于死亡\n 1b) 安全带出\n 1c) 免于疾病\n2) 从形而上的危险中拯拯救出来\n 2a) 拯救人或物\n   2a1) 神或基督的拯救\n   2a2) 人作为属天拯救的协调者\n 2b) (被动) 被拯救, 得到救赎\n3) 有些经文同时包含(1)与(2)的意思 (#可 8:35;路 9:24,56; 罗 9:27; 林前 3:15|)\n ',	'4982 sozo {sode\'-zo}\n\nDerived from the root type SOS (an abbreviation of the obsolete word saoz, meaning “safe”);\n TDNT - 7:965 ,1132; verb\nAV - save 93, make whole 9, heal 3, be whole 2, misc 3; 110\n\n1) Rescue, preservation, rescue from danger and natural disasters\n 1a) Freedom from death\n 1b) Take out safety\n 1c) Immunity from disease\n2) Saved from metaphysical dangers\n 2a) Save people or things\n 2a1) Salvation by God or Christ\n 2a2) Man as coordinator of heavenly salvation\n 2b) Be (passive) saved, and be redeemed\n3) Some verses contain the meaning of both (1) and (2) (#可 8:35; Luke 9:24 ,56; Romans 9:27; 1 Lin 3:15 |)',	1),
(5903,	'04983',	'4983 soma {so\'-mah}\n\n源于 4982; TDNT - 7:1024,1140; 中性名词\n\nAV - body 144, bodily 1, slave 1; 146\n\n1) 指人或动物的身体\n  1a) 尸体\n  1b) 活着的身体\n2) 奴隶 (#启 18:13|)      \n3) (植物与种子的结构) 身体\n4) (用于身体投射出影子的意象) 事物本身, 实体 (#西 2:17|)\n5) (团结的一群人) 身体',	'4983 soma {so\'-mah}\n\nDerived from 4982; TDNT - 7:1024 ,1140; neutral noun\n\nAV - body 144, bodily 1, slave 1; 146\n\n1) Refers to the body of a human or animal\n 1a) Corpse\n 1b) Alive body\n2) Slave (#启 18:13 |) \n3) Body (structure of plants and seeds)\n4) (for images of bodies casting shadows) the thing itself, the entity (#西 2:17 |)\n5) Body (a group of people united)',	1),
(5904,	'05019',	'5019 Tarsos {tar-sos\'}\n\n或许与 tarsos(平底篮子) 同; 专有地名\n\nAV - Tarsus 3; 3\n\n大数= \"平底篮子\"\n1) 在西里西亚的一个主要城巿，也是保罗的出生地及早年的家乡。\n   使徒行传 9:11; 21:39; 22:3. 甚至在希腊历史的兴盛时期曾\n   是个重要城巿。在罗马内战时，它是属该撒这一边的，而且在\n　 该撒来访的时候，改了城巿的名为茱利奥波利斯。亚古士督让\n   这城成为自由城巿。在早期罗马皇帝统辖之下，是个着名的教\n   育城。斯特拉波将它视为与雅典及亚历山大港一样的。大数也\n   是繁荣的商业地。位于西德努斯河岸之宽阔与肥沃的平原上。\n   如今没什么重要的遗迹存留。',	'5019 Tarsos {tar-sos\'}\n\nPerhaps the same as tarsos (flat baskets); proprietary place names\n\nAV - Tarsus 3; 3\n\nlarge number = “flat basket”\n1) In one of the major cities of Silesia, it is also the birthplace of Paul and his hometown in his early years.\n Acts 9:11; 21:39; 22:3. Even in the heyday of Greek history\n It\'s an important city. It was on the side of Caesar during the Roman Civil War, and in\n When Caesar visited, the name of the city was changed to Juliopolis. Agus Jean\n This city became Liberty City. It was a famous religion under the rule of the early Roman emperors\n YUKI. Strabo sees it as the same as Athens and Alexandria. Osuya\n It\'s a thriving commercial area. Located on a wide and fertile plain on the banks of the Sidenus River.\n There are no important ruins left today.',	1),
(5905,	'05020',	'5020 tartaroo {tar-tar-o\'-o}\n\n源自 Tartaros (地狱中最底的渊薮); 动词\n\nAV - cast down to hell 1; 1\n\n1) Tartaros是希腊人认为比阴府还要低深的一处地方,\n   是神明执行审判之处.以色列的天启文学也提到这样\n   的地方.\n2) 被关在,打入Tartaros(#彼后 2:4|)',	'5020 tartaroo {tar-tar-o\'-o}\n\nDerived from Tartaros (the bottom of hell); verb\n\nAV - cast down to hell 1; 1\n\n1) Tartaros is a place considered by the Greeks to be even lower than the Yin Province,\n It is the place where the gods carry out their judgment. This is also mentioned in Israel\'s Apocalypse literature\n The place to.\n2) Get locked up, hit Tartaros (#彼后 2:4 |)',	1),
(5906,	'05029',	'5029 tacha {takh\'-ah}\n\n可能是 5036(作副词) 的中性复数; 副词\n\nAV - peradventure 1, perhaps 1; 2\n\n1)或者, 也许.',	'5029 tacha {takh\'-ah}\n\nMay be the neutral plural of 5036 (adverb); adverb\n\nAV - peradventure 1, 1; 2\n\n1) Alternatively, maybe.',	1),
(5907,	'05056',	'5056 telos {tel\'-os}\n\n源于原形的 tello (设定一个明确的终点或目标);\n   TDNT - 8:49,1161; 中性名词\n\nAV - end 35, custom 3, uttermost 1, finally 1, ending 1,\n     by (one\'s) continual + 1519 1; 42\n\n1) 结束, 中止, 终结\n2) (过程的最后一部分) 结尾\n3) 目标, 结局, 终点\n4) 余下的 (#林前15:24|)\n5) 税, 劳力税, 税责 (#太17:25;罗13:7;林前10:11|) ',	'5056 telos {tel\'-os}\n\ntello from the prototype (set a clear end point or goal);\n TDNT - 8:49 ,1161; neutral noun\n\nAV - end 35, custom 3, uttermost 1, finally 1, ending 1,\n by (one\'s) continual + 1519 1; 42\n\n1) Termination, Suspension, Termination\n2) End of (the last part of the process)\n3) Goals, endings, and endings\n4) Remaining (#林前15:24|)\n5) Tax, Labor Tax, Tax Liability (#太17:25; Romans 13:7; Forests 10:11 |)',	1),
(5908,	'00459',	'459 anomos {an\'-om-os}\n\n源于 1 (作 否定词 质词/语助词) 和 3551; TDNT - 4:1086,646; 形容词\n\nAV - without law 4, transgressor 2, wicked 2, lawless 1, unlawful 1; 10\n\n1) 律法之外, 没有律法的(#林前 9:21)\n2) 偏离律法的, 目无法纪的\n 2a) 指神的道德律法\n 2b) 指在以色列法统之外的人\n3) 不法之总代表(#帖后 2:8|)',	'459 anomos {an\'-om-os}\n\nDerived from 1 (as negative/slang auxiliary) and 3551; TDNT - 4:1086 ,646; adjectives\n\nAV - without law 4, transgressor 2, wicked 2, lawless 1, abused 1; 10\n\n1) Other than the law, there is no law (#林前 9:21)\n2) Those who deviate from the law and are undisciplined\n 2a) Refers to God\'s moral law\n 2b) Refers to persons outside the legal system of Israel\n3) General Representative of the Wrongful (#帖后 2:8 |)',	1),
(5909,	'04347',	'4347 proskollao {pros-kol-lah\'-o}\n\n源自 4314 与 2853; TDNT - 3:823,452; 动词\n\nAV - cleave 2, be joined 1, join (one\'s) self 1; 4\n\n1) 字意:黏着于\n2) 与...连合, 忠心投身于..., 信守于...',	'4347 proskollao {pros-kol-lah\'-o}\n\nDerived from 4314 vs 2853; TDNT - 3:823,452; verb\n\nAV - Cleave 2, be joined 1, join (one\'s) self 1; 4\n\n1) Word meaning: stick to\n2) Join with..., devote yourself faithfully to..., stick to...',	1),
(5910,	'04366',	'4366 prosregnumi {pros-rayg\'-noo-mee}\n\n源自 4314 与 4486; 动词\n\nAV - beat vehemently upon 1, beat vehemently against 1; 2\n\n1) 打破击碎\n2) 突然临头  (#路 6:48-49|)',	'4366 prosregnumi {pros-rayg\'-noo-mee}\n\nDerived from 4314 and 4486; verbs\n\nAV - beat vehemently upon 1, beat vehemently against 1; 2\n\n1) Break Shatter\n2) Suddenly Coming (#路 6:48-49 |)',	1),
(5911,	'04762',	'4762 strepho {stref\'-o}\n\n源自 5157 加强型; TDNT - 7:714,1093; 动词\n\nAV - turn 11, turn (one\'s) self 2, turn (one) 1, turn again 1,\n     turn back again 1, turn (one) about 1, be converted 1,\n     vr turn 1; 19\n \n1) 转动\n 1a) 将....转向 (#太 5:39|)\n 1b) 回转, 转向\n2) 带回, 归回 (原先的位置) ( #太 27:3|) \n3) 将....转变为 (#启 11:6|)\n4) 转离  ( #徒 7:42| )\n5) 内在的转变 ( #太 18:3 | )\n',	'4762 strepho {stref\'-o}\n\nFrom 5157 reinforced; TDNT - 7:714 ,1093; verb\n\nAV - turn 11, turn (one\'s) self 2, turn (one) 1, turn again 1,\n turn back again 1, turn (one) about 1, be aware 1,\n VR turn 1; 19\n \n1) Rotate\n 1a) Turn... (#太 5:39 |)\n 1b) rotation, steering\n2) Bring Back, Return (Original Position) (#太 27:3 |) \n3) Change... to (#启 11:6 |)\n4) Transfer (#徒 7:42 |)\n5) Inner Transformation (#太 18:3 |)',	1),
(5912,	'04811',	'4811 sukophanteo {soo-kof-an-teh\'-o}\n\n源自4810的复合型与5316的衍生字; TDNT - 7:759,1100; 动词\n\nAV - accuse falsely 1, take by false accusation 1; 2\n\n1) 骚扰,压榨,恐吓 (#路 3:14|)\n2) 敲诈,勒索 (#路 19:8|)\n\n在雅典有群人称为\"sukophantia\",专门打探有谁从希腊的阿提卡区(Attica)\n往外运输无花果.有时这些人也会勒索那些怕被揭发的人. 从希腊剧作家阿里\n斯托芬(Aristophanes)时起,\"sukophantes\"就泛指那些恶棍或喜欢敲诈的人. ',	'4811 sukophanteo {soo-kof-an-teh\'-o}\n\nCompound form derived from 4810 and derivative of 5316; TDNT - 7:759 ,1100; verb\n\nAV - accuse falsely 1, take by false accusation 1; 2\n\n1) Harassment, Squeezing, Intimidation (#路 3:14 |)\n2) Extortion, Extortion (#路 19:8 |)\n\nThere is a group of people in Athens called “sukophantia”, specifically to find out who is from the Attica district of Greece\nTransporting figs out of the country. Sometimes these people also extort people who are afraid of being exposed. From the Greek playwright Ali\nFrom the time of Aristophanes, “sukophantes” generally referred to villains or people who like to extort money.',	1),
(5913,	'04934',	'4934 suntithemai {soon-tith\'-em-ahee}\n\n源自 5087 与 4862 关身语态; 动词\n\nAV - agree 2, covenant 1, assent 1; 4\n\n1) 并放在一起\n2) (双方皆同意的约) 同意 (#路 22:5|) \n3) (大家一起达成的) 决定 (#约 9:22; 徒 23:20|)\n4) (以同意表达支持) 同意 (#徒 24:9|) ',	'4934 suntithemai {soon-tith\'-em-ahee}\n\nFrom 5087 and 4862 off the body voice; verb\n\nAV - agree 2, covenant 1, assent 1; 4\n\n1) and put them together\n2) Consent (a covenant agreed by both parties) (#路 22:5 |) \n3) Decisions (reached together) (#约 9:22; Acts 23:20 |)\n4) (Show support by consent) Agree (#徒 24:9 |)',	1),
(5914,	'04947',	'4947 Suria {soo-ree\'-ah}\n\n可能源自希伯来文 06865; 专有地名\n\nAV - Syria 8; 8\n\n叙利亚 = \"高举的\"\n1) 亚洲的一区, 北边界为Taurus(山脉),\n   东边是幼发拉底河地区, 南边界是巴勒斯坦, \n   西边以地中海为界.主后64年成为罗马一省,定都于安提阿',	'4947 Suria {soo-ree\'-ah}\n\nMay derive from Hebrew 06865; proprietary place name\n\nAV - Syria 8; 8\n\nSyria = “exalted”\n1) A region in Asia, the northern boundary is Taurus (mountain range),\n the Euphrates region to the east, Palestine to the south, \n It is bordered by the Mediterranean Sea to the west. It became a province of Rome in \'64, and its capital is Antioch',	1),
(5915,	'05261',	'5261 hupogrammos {hoop-og-ram-mos\'}\n\n源自 259 的复合字 与 1125; TDNT - 1:772,128; 阳性名词\n\nAV - example 1; 1\n\n1) (字意) 写字的范本, 包括字母表的所有字母, 作为给初学者学习描写的辅助\n2) 模范 (#彼前2:21|)',	'5261 hupogrammos {hoop-og-ram-mos\'}\n\nCompound words derived from 259 and 1125; TDNT - 1:772 ,128; positive nouns\n\nAV - example 1; 1\n\n1) A sample of (literal) writing, including all the letters of the alphabet, as an aid for beginners to learn to describe\n2) Model (#彼前2:21|)',	1),
(5916,	'05415',	'5415 Phortounatos {for-too-nat\'-os}\n\n源自拉丁文; 阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Fortunatus 2; 2\n\n福徒拿都 = \"装得满满的\"\n1) 哥林多的一位基督徒 (#林前 16:17|)',	'5415 Phortounatos {for-too-nat\'-os}\n\nDerived from Latin; proper noun for masculinity\n\nAV - Fortunatus 2; 2\n\nFotonadu = “Filled”\n1) A Christian from Corinthians (#林前 16:17 |)',	1),
(5917,	'05438',	'5438 phulake {foo-lak-ay\'}\n\n源于 5442; TDNT - 9:241,1280; 阴性名词\n\nAV - prison 36, watch 6, imprisonment 2, hold 1, cage 1, ward 1; 47\n\n1) 看守\n2) 负责警戒的人, 卫兵, 哨兵\n3) 牢房\n4) 守夜\n  4a) 指夜晚轮班看守的时段.早期时, 希腊人将一夜分成三个时段, 在被掳之前, \n      以色列人亦在每晚安排有三个巡更的卫班; 但是到了罗马统治的时代, 他们\n      采行了马的习惯, 在每夜安排四个巡更的班次.',	'5438 phulake {foo-lak-ay\'}\n\nDerived from 5442; TDNT - 9:241 ,1280; negative noun\n\nAV - Prison 36, Watch 6, Prison 2, Hold 1, Cage 1, Ward 1; 47\n\n1) Warden\n2) Person in charge of vigilance, guard, sentry\n3) Cells\n4) Vigil\n 4a) refers to the period of night shift guards. In the early days, the Greeks divided the night into three periods, and before being taken prisoner, \n The Israelis also scheduled three patrols per night; but by the time of Roman rule, they\n Adopting the habit of horses, scheduling four patrols per night.',	1),
(5918,	'05158',	'5158 tropos {trop\'-os}\n\n与 5157 同源; 阳性名词\n\nAV - as + 3739 3, even as + 2596 + 3739 2, way 2, means 2,\n     even as + 3739 1, in like manner as + 3639 1, manner 1,\n     conversation 1; 13\n\n1) 方式, 方法, 种类\n2) 生活方式，人格品行，举止 (#来13:5|)',	'5158 tropos {trop\'-os}\n\nHomologous with 5157; masculine noun\n\nAV - as + 3739 3, even as + 2596 + 3739 2, way 2, means 2,\n even as + 3739 1, in like manner as + 3639 1, manner 1,\n conversation 1; 13\n\n1) Methods, methods, types\n2) Lifestyle, personality, and manners (#来13:5|)',	1),
(5919,	'05190',	'5190 Tuchikos {too-khee-kos\'}\n\n源自 5177 的衍生字; 阳性专有名词\n\n钦定本 - Tychicus 7; 7\n\n推基古 = \"决定命运的\"\n1) 从亚细亚省份来的基督徒, 是使徒保罗的朋友与同伴',	'5190 Tuchikos {too-khee-kos\'}\n\nDerived from 5177; positive proper noun\n\nThe definitive book - Tychicus 7; 7\n\nPush Kigu = “the one who decides the fate”\n1) Christians from the provinces of Asia are friends and companions of the Apostle Paul',	1),
