(5958,	'00599',	'599 apothnesko {ap-oth-nace\'-ko}\n\n源自 575 与 2348; TDNT - 3:7,312; 动词\n\nAV - die 98, be dead 29, be at the point of death + 3195 1,\n     perish 1, lie a dying 1, be slain + 5408 1, vr dead 1; 112\n\n1) 死\n 1a) 人自然的死亡\n 1b) 属灵的死\n2) 将死, 面临死亡, 必死 (#林前 15:31; 林后 6:9; 来 7:8|)   \n\n   ',	'599 apothnesko {ap-oth-nace\'-en}\n\nFrom 575 vs 2348; TDNT - 3:7 ,312; verb\n\nAV - die 98, be dead 29, be at the point of death + 3195 1,\n Perish 1, Lie A Dying 1, Be Slain+5408 1, VR Dead 1; 112\n\n1) Death\n 1a) The natural death of a person\n 1b) Spiritual death\n2) Will die, face death, must die (#林前 15:31; After the Forest 6:9; Come 7:8 |)',	1),
(5959,	'00697',	'697 Areios Pagos {ar\'-i-os pag\'-os}\n\n源自 Ares (希腊战神的名字)以及与4078相关的字; 专有地名\n\nAV - Areopagus 1, Mars Hill 1; 2\n\n亚略古巴 = \"战神之巅\"\n1) 雅典一处多石的高地,在神殿西侧的正对面(#徒 17:19,22|).\n   此处亦称为\"战神山\",因为相传战神因为海神的儿子企图染指\n   其女,而杀了他.战神于此接受十二神只的审判.',	'697 Areios Pagos {ar\'-i-os pag\'-os}\n\nDerived from Ares (the name of the Greek god of war) and words related to 4078; proprietary place name\n\nAV - Areopagus 1, Mars Hill 1; 2\n\nAllio Cuba = “On top of God of War”\n1) A stony high ground in Athens, directly opposite the west side of the temple (#徒 17:19 ,22|).\n This is also known as “Ares Mountain” because according to legend, the god of war attempted to infect his finger because of Poseidon\'s son\n his daughter, and killed him. The God of War was then judged by the Twelve Gods.',	1),
(5960,	'00886',	'886 acheiropoietos {akh-i-rop-oy\'-ay-tos}\n\n源于 1 (作否定质词/语助词) 和 5499; TDNT - 9:436,1309; 形容词\n\nAV - made without hands 2, not made with hands 1; 3\n\n1) 非手工作的, 不是人手可以做得出来的 (#可 14:58; 林后 5:1; 西 2:11|)',	'886 acheiropoietos {akh-i-rop-oy\'-ay-tos}\n\nDerived from 1 (as negative/slang auxiliary) and 5499; TDNT - 9:436, 1309; adjectives\n\nAV - made without hands 2, not made with hands 1; 3\n\n1) Non-manual work, not something that can be done by hand (#可 14:58; After Forest 5:1; West 2:11 |)',	1),
(5961,	'01525',	'1525 eiserchomai {ice-er\'-khom-ahee}\n\n源于 1519 和 2064; TDNT - 2:676,257; 动词\n\nAV - enter 107, go 22, come in 19, go in 18, enter in 17,\n     come 14, arise 1;  198\n\n1) 出去或进来: 进入\n   1a) 指人或动物, 进入一个屋子或城市\n   1b) 指撒旦掌控一个人的肉体\n   1c) 指事物: 比如食物被吃入口中\n2) 隐喻.\n   2a) 指进入任何一种状况, 状态, 社会, 或职业\n       2a1) 兴起, 出生, 成为\n       2a2) 指人来到群众面前\n       2a3) 指进入生命之中(有了生命)\n   2b) 进入心中的意念或想法',	'1525 eiserchomai {ice-er\'-khom-ahee}\n\nfrom 1519 and 2064; TDNT - 2:676 ,257; verb\n\nAV - enter 107, go 22, come in 19, go in 18, enter in 17,\n come 14, arise 1; 198\n\n1) Go out or come in: Enter\n 1a) Refers to a person or animal entering a house or city\n 1b) refers to Satan taking control of a person\'s body\n 1c) Refers to things: such as food being eaten in the mouth\n2) Metaphors.\n 2a) means entering any kind of status, state, society, or occupation\n 2a1) Rise, be born, become\n 2a2) Refers to people coming to the masses\n 2a3) refers to entering life (having a life)\n 2b) Thoughts or thoughts that enter the mind',	1),
