(5979,	'03017',	'3017 Leui {lyoo\'-ee}\n\n源于希伯来文 03878; TDNT - 4:234,529;阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Levi 5; 5\n\n利未 = \"连结的\"\n1) 族长雅各和其妻利亚所生的第三个儿子, 是以色列人利未支派的始祖\n2) 麦基的儿子, 耶稣的祖先之一 (#路 3:24|)\n3) 西缅的儿子, 耶稣的祖先之一 (#路 3:30|)\n',	'3017 Lei {lyoo\'-ee}\n\nFrom Hebrew 03878; TDNT - 4:234 ,529; positive proper noun\n\nAV - Levi 5; 5\n\nliwei = “linked”\n1) The third son of the patriarch Jacob and his wife, Leah, was the ancestor of the tribe of the Levites of Israel\n2) Son of McKee, one of the ancestors of Jesus (#路 3:24 |)\n3) Simon\'s son, one of the ancestors of Jesus (#路 3:30 |)',	1),
(5980,	'03033',	'3033 Libue {lib-oo\'-ay}\n\n可能源自 3047; 专有地名\n\nAV - Libya 1; 1\n\n吕彼亚= \"哭泣受折磨的\"\n1) 位于北非并围绕埃及宽大的一地. 其首都为塞利尼(Cyrene), \n因此称为塞利尼的吕比亚(Libya Cyrenaica) (#徒 2:10|)',	'3033 Libue {lib-oo\'-ay}\n\nPossibly derived from 3047; proprietary place name\n\nAV - Libya 1; 1\n\nLupia = “The Tormented Crying”\n1) Located in North Africa and generously surrounding Egypt. Its capital is Cyrene (Cyrene), \nHence the name of Libya (Libya Cyrenaica) (#徒 2:10 |)',	1),
(5981,	'03370',	'3370 Medos {may\'-dos}\n\n源自外来语 参 04074; 阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Mede 1; 1\n\n米底亚人 = \"中间土地\"\n1) 住在米底亚的居民, 该处有犹太人侨居地 (#徒 2:9|)',	'3370 Medos {may\'-dos}\n\nDerived from foreign language ginseng 04074; positive proper noun\n\nAV - Mede 1; 1\n\nMidian = “Middle Land”\n1) Residents living in Midia, where there is a Jewish diaspora (#徒 2:9 |)',	1),
(5982,	'03581',	'3581 xenos {xen\'-os}\n\n显然是一个字根; TDNT - 5:1,661; 形容词\n\nAV - stranger 10, strange 3, host 1; 14\n\n\n1)形容词\n 1a) 陌生的\n   1a1) 源于外界的 (#徒 17:18; 来 13:9|)\n   1a2) 未曾听闻的 (#彼前 4:12|)\n 1b) 不熟悉, 陌生的 (#弗 2:12|)\n\n2)实名词\n 2a) 陌生人, 外国人\n 2b) (慷慨款待外人的) 主人 (#罗 16:23)',	'3581 xenos {xen\'-os}\n\nApparently a root word; TDNT - 5:1 ,661; adjective\n\nAV - Stranger 10, Strange 3, Host 1; 14\n\n\n1) Adjectives\n 1a) Strange\n 1a1) from the outside world (#徒 17:18; come 13:9 |)\n 1a2) Unheard of (#彼前 4:12 |)\n 1b) Unfamiliar, Strange (#弗 2:12 |)\n\n2) Real nouns\n 2a) Stranger, foreigner\n 2b) Owner (who treats outsiders generously) (#罗 16:23)',	1),
(5983,	'03957',	'3957 pascha {pas\'-khah}\n\n源于亚兰文, 参 06453; TDNT - 5:896,797; 中性名词\n\nAV - Passover 28, Easter 1; 29\n\n1) 逾越节 (习俗上用以纪念以色列人的祖先被从埃及带领出来)\n2) 逾越节的羔羊, 亦即 以色列人习俗上在尼散月(每年的第一个月)十四日所宰杀而吃的羔羊,\n   用以纪念他们的先祖在准备离开埃及前, 依神的命令而宰吃羔羊, 并将其血洒在门楣上, 当\n   灭命天使见到这血时, 就越过该户; 基督的上十架被比喻为这被杀的逾越节羔羊\n3) 逾越节的晚餐\n4) 逾越节的筵席, 为纪念逾越节而有的筵席, 由尼散月十四日一直进行到廿日',	'3957 pascha {pas\'-khah}\n\nDerived from Aramaic, ginseng 06453; TDNT - 5:896 ,797; neutral noun\n\nAV - Passover 28, Easter 1; 29\n\n1) Passover (customarily used to commemorate the fact that the ancestors of the Israelites were led out of Egypt)\n2) The Passover lamb, that is, the lamb that the Israelis eat slaughtered on the 14th of the month of Nisan (the first month of each year)\n in honor of their ancestors who slaughtered lambs at the command of God before preparing to leave Egypt and spilled their blood on the lintel,\n When the angel of destruction saw the blood, he crossed the house; the ten of Christ were likened to the slain Passover Lamb\n3) Passover dinner\n4) The Passover feast, which is held to commemorate the Passover, will be held from the 14th to the 20th of the month of Nisan',	1),
