(5986,	'02596',	'2596 kata {kat-ah\'}\n\n介系词\n\nAV - according to 107, after 61, against 58, in 36, by 27,\n     daily + 2250 15, as 11, misc 165; 480\n\n1. 接直接受词: 根据, 按照, 合乎, 关于, 正如,\n2. 与数目字或地方连用时: 在...里; 为了; 为了...目的;\n   在, 大约(时间); 在...上, 沿着, 遍及, 向; 离, 面对;\n3. 接所有格: 反对, 敌对; 下, 从...下; (传)遍; 指着...\n    (发誓); 控告; (有权) 办 (人).',	'2596 kata {kat-ah\'}\n\nIntermediary words\n\nAV - according to 107, after 61, against 58, in 36, by 27,\n daily+2250 15, as 11, misc 165; 480\n\n1. Receipt: according to, according to, reasonable, about, just as,\n2. When used in conjunction with numbers or places: in; for; for... purpose;\n at, approximately (time); on, along, all over, towards; away, face;\n3. Receiving Possessive: Opposing, Hostile; Down, From Down; (Biography) All Over; Pointing at...\n (swear); charge; (have the right to) act (person).',	1),
(5987,	'00142',	'142 airo {ah\'-ee-ro}\n\n字根型; TDNT - 1:185,28; 动词\n\n钦定本 - take up 32, take away 25, take 25, away with 5, lift up 4,\n     bear 3, misc 8; 102\n\n1) 举起, 提起, 提高\n   1a) 字义的 - 例: 石头\n   1b) 喻意的\n2) 从一个地点拿起, 带到另一地点\n   2a) 携带 (字义的)\n   2b) 带走, 挪移 (字义的)\n3) (强行) 带走, 移除\n4) 取走 (商业性的) (#路 19:21|)\n5) 悬移不定 (#约 10:24|)\n6) 收锚, 离开 (#徒 27:13|)',	'142 airo {ah\'-ee-ro}\n\nroot; TDNT - 1:185 ,28; verb\n\nChin Dingben - Take Up 32, Take Away 25, Take 25, Away With 5, Lift Up 4,\n bear 3, misc 8; 102\n\n1) Lift, lift, raise\n 1a) Meaning - Example: stone\n 1b) figurative\n2) Pick up from one location and bring to another\n 2a) carry (literal)\n 2b) Take away, shift (literal)\n3) (forcibly) take away, remove\n4) Take away (commercial) (#路 19:21 |)\n5) Indefinite shift (#约 10:24 |)\n6) Close anchor and leave (#徒 27:13 |)',	1),
(5988,	'01921',	'1921 epiginosko {ep-ig-in-oce\'-ko}\n\n源自 1909 与 1097; TDNT - 1:689,119; 动词\n\nAV - know 30, acknowledge 5, perceive 3, take knowledge of 2,\n     have knowledge of 1, know well 1; 42\n\n1) 认识, 知道\n2) 发现, 得知\n3) 体认, 重新认识, 熟知\n4) 敬重 (#太 17:12; 林前 16:18|)\n5) 明白, 了解 (#徒 25:10; 林后 1:13|)',	'1921 epiginosko {ep-ig-in-oce\'-ko}\n\nFrom 1909 vs 1097; TDNT - 1:689 ,119; verb\n\nAV - know 30, know 5, take knowledge of 2,\n have knowledge of 1, know well 1; 42\n\n1) Know, know\n2) Discover, learn\n3) Recognize, re-recognize, and be familiar\n4) Respect (#太 17:12; Forests 16:18 |)\n5) Understand, Understand (#徒 25:10; After Forest 1:13 |)',	1),
