(5990,	'00139',	'139 hairesis {hah\'-ee-res-is}\n\n源于 138; TDNT - 1:180,27; 阴性名词\n\nAV - sect 5, heresy 4; 9\n\n1) 遵循某个共同的教义或宗旨原则的群体(教派或党派)\n 1a) 撒都该人(犹太教派之一, 不信有复活)\n 1b) 异端\n 1c) 歧见,分裂(#林前 11:19; 加 5:20|)\n5) 看法,教条(#彼后 2:1|)',	'139 hairesis {hah\'-ee-res-is}\n\nDerived from 138; TDNT - 1:180 ,27; negative noun\n\nAV - Sect 5, heresy 4; 9\n\n1) A group (sect or party) that adheres to a common doctrine or purpose\n 1a) Sadducees (one of the Jewish denominations, there is a resurrection without faith)\n 1b) Heresy\n 1c) Disagreement, division (#林前 11:19; plus 5:20 |)\n5) Views, Dogma (#彼后 2:1 |)',	1),
(5991,	'00141',	'141 hairetikos {hahee-ret-ee-kos\'}\n\n与140同源; TDNT - 1:184,27; 形容词\n\nAV - that is a heretic 1; 1\n\n1) 制造分裂,好结党的(#多 3:10|)',	'141 hairetikos {hahee-ret-ee-kos\'}\n\nHomologous with 140; TDNT - 1:184 ,27; adjective\n\nAV - that is a heretic 1; 1\n\n1) Creating Divisions, and Partying Well (#多 3:10 |)',	1),
(5992,	'04099',	'4099 Pisidia {pis-id-ee\'-ah}\n\n可能源自外来语; 专有名词 地名\n\nAV - Pisidia 2; 2\n\n彼西底= \"漆黑的\"\n1) 位于小亚细亚的一个地区, 由旁非利亚(Pamphylia), 旁非利亚海(Pamphylian\n   Sea), 弗吕家(Phrygia), 和力卡奥尼亚(Lycaonia)所环绕 (#徒 13:14, 14:24|)',	'4099 Pisidia {pis-id-ee\'-ah}\n\nMay be derived from a foreign language; proper nouns place names\n\nAV - Pisidia 2; 2\n\npicedes = “dark”\n1) Located in a region of Asia Minor, by the Pamphylia (Pamphylia), the Punjabi Sea (Pamphylian)\n Sea), Phrygia (Phrygia), and Lycaonia (#徒 13:14, 14:24 |)',	1),
(5993,	'04337',	'4337 prosecho {pros-ekh\'-o}\n\n源于 4314 和 2192; 动词\n\nAV - beware 7, give heed to 5, take heed to 3, give heed unto 1,\n     take heed 1, take heed unto 1, take heed whereunto + 3739 1,\n     misc 5; 24\n\n1) 担心, 关切, 照顾 \n2) 专注心思, 专心留意\n3) 忙于, 投身于, 陷于 #提前 3:8,4:13; 来 7:13|',	'4337 Prosecho {pros-ekh\'-o}\n\nOriginated from 4314 and 2192; verbs\n\nAV - beware 7, give heed to 5, take heed to 3, give heed unto 1,\n take heed 1, take heed unto 1, take heed whereunto + 3739 1,\n misc 5; 24\n\n1) Worry, concern, care \n2) Concentrate on your mind and pay attention\n3) Be busy, devote yourself to, get stuck in #提前 3:8, 4:13; come 7:13 |',	1),
(5994,	'04904',	'4904 sunergos {soon-er-gos\'}\n\n源于被认为是 4862 的复合字 和 2041 字根; TDNT - 7:871,1116; 形容词\n\nAV - fellowlabourer 4, helper 3, fellowhelper 2, fellowworkers 1,\n     workfellow 1, labourer together with 1, companion in labour 1; 13\n\n1) 帮助的\n 1a) 在新约圣经都是实名词: 工作上的伙伴, 同工',	'4904 sunergos {soon-er-gos\'}\n\nDerived from compound words thought to be 4862 and root 2041; TDNT - 7:871 ,1116; adjectives\n\nAV - fellowlabourer 4, helper 3, fellowhelper 2, fellowworkers 1,\n workfellow 1, labourer together with 1, companion in labour 1; 13\n\n1) Helpful\n 1a) In the New Testament are all real terms: partners at work, co-workers',	1),
(5995,	'05177',	'5177 tugchano {toong-khan\'-o}\n\n可能源于一已不使用的 tucho (另一型teucho的关身语态 [作好准备或使过关], 用于特定\n的时态中, 在\'造成影响\'的意义上近似 5088 的字源); TDNT - 8:238,1191; 动词\n\nAV - obtain 5, be 1, chance 1, little 1, enjoy 1, may be 1, not tr 1,\n     misc 2; 13\n\n1) 得到, 遇见, 发现\n3) 碰巧, 发生, 结果是\n   ',	'5177 tugchano {toong-khan\'-o}\n\nMay be derived from a tucho that is no longer in use (another type of teucho\'s closed voice [prepare or pass]), used to specify\napproximates the origin of 5088 in the sense of \'cause impact\'); TDNT - 8:238 ,1191; verb\n\nAV - 5, be 1, chance 1, little 1, enjoy 1, may be 1, not tr 1,\n misc 2; 13\n\n1) Get, Meet, Discover\n3) By chance, it happens, it turns out',	1),
(5996,	'05316',	'5316 phaino {fah\'-ee-no}\n\n源于 05457 字根的扩张型; TDNT - 9:1,1244; 动词\n\n钦定本 - appear 17, shine 10, be seen 2, seem 1, think 1; 31\n\n1) 照亮, 闪亮\n2) 出现, 显现, 成为可见的\n3) 被认出, 被显示, 被显明\n4) 看起来是 (与实情相反)\n4) 看起来, 似乎 (#可 14:64|)\n\n其同义词, 见 05837',	'5316 phaino {fah\'-ee-no}\n\nExpanded form from the root of 05457; TDNT - 9:1 ,1244; verb\n\nChin Dingben - appear 17, shine 10, be seen 2, seem 1, think 1; 31\n\n1) Illuminate, shine\n2) Appear, manifest, and become visible\n3) Be recognised, shown, and revealed\n4) Looks like it is (contrary to the truth)\n4) Looks, Seems (#可 14:64 |)\n\nFor synonyms, see 05837',	1),
(5997,	'00021',	'21 agalliao {ag-al-lee-ah\'-o}\n\n源自 agan (多) 与 242; TDNT - 1:19, *; 动词\n\n钦定本 - rejoice 7, be exceeding glad 1, be glad 1, greatly rejoice 1,\n     with exceeding joy 1; 11\n\n1)兴高采烈, 极度欢欣, 欢喜快乐',	'21 agalliao {ag-al-lee-ah\'-o}\n\nDerived from agan (more) with 242; TDNT - 1:19, *; verb\n\nAdoribon - rejoice 7, be glad 1, be glad 1, glad rejoice 1,\n with joy 1; 11\n\n1) Cheerful, extremely joyful, joyful',	1),
(5998,	'04102',	'4102 pistis {pis\'-tis}\n\n源自 03982; TDNT - 6:174,849; 阴性名词\n\n钦定本 - faith 239, assurance 1, believe + 1537 1, belief 1,\n     them that believe 1, fidelity 1; 244\n\n1) 对任何真理的坚信, 相信;\n   在新约里, 是针对人与神的关系, 以及属神的事的坚信和相信,\n   一般都包含着信靠的观念, 以及由相信而生的神圣火热, 并加入其中\n   1a) 与神有关\n       1a1) 坚信神的存在, 以及神是万有的创造者和统治者,\n            是藉着基督的永恒救恩的供应者和赠与者\n   1b) 与基督有关\n       1b1) 一种强烈的和欣然接受的坚信或相信耶稣就是那一位弥赛亚,\n            我们藉着他在神的国度里得到永恒的救恩\n   1c) 基督教的信仰\n   1d) 对神或基督的那种信靠 (或是信心), 是从对神和基督的信心所发出的\n2) 忠贞, 忠实\n   2a) 能让人信靠的个性',	'4102 pistis {pis\'-tis}\n\nFrom 03982; TDNT - 6:174 ,849; negative noun\n\nQindingben - faith 239, assurance 1, believe + 1537 1,\n them that believe 1, fidelity 1; 244\n\n1) a firm belief in any truth, belief;\n In the New Testament, it refers to the relationship between man and God, and the firm belief and belief in God\'s affairs,\n It generally includes the idea of trustworthiness, and the sacred fiery born of faith, and joins it\n 1a) Relating to God\n 1a1) Convinced that God exists and that God is the creator and ruler of all things,\n Providers and givers of eternal salvation through Christ\n 1b) Relating to Christ\n 1b1) A strong and graciously accepted belief or belief that Jesus is the Messiah,\n We receive eternal salvation through him in the kingdom of God\n 1c) The Christian Faith\n 1d) The kind of trust (or faith) in God or Christ emanates from faith in God and Christ\n2) Faithful, faithful\n 2a) Personality that people can trust',	1),
(5999,	'04437',	'4437 puknos {pook-nos\'}\n\n与 4635 同源; 形容词\n\nAV - often 2, oftener 1; 3\n\n1) 频繁的, 多次的',	'4437 puknos {pook-nos\'}\n\nSame as 4635; adjective\n\nAV - often 2, oftener 1; 3\n\n1) Frequent, multiple times',	1),
(6000,	'04716',	'4716 stauros {stow-ros\'}\n\n源于 2476 的字根; TDNT - 7:572,1071; 阳性名词\n\nAV - cross 28; 28\n\n1) 原意: 直立的桩子, 柱子\n2) 十字架\n   2a) 希腊人和罗马人由腓尼基人处所引入的一种以极端残忍及羞辱而着名的刑具; 成为罗马帝国所使用\n       的刑罚之一, 直到康士坦丁大帝时才废止, 用于十恶不赦之罪犯, 尤其如社会最低阶层的如隶, \n       强盗, 教嗦或带头叛乱的人, 在偶而的情形下于各行省中, 因着统治长官的个人好恶, 正直和平\n       顺的人, 甚至罗马公民, 也有被施以此刑的.\n   2b) 基督所承受的十字架刑罚\n   2c) 信徒追随被钉的主所承受的苦难',	'4716 stauros {stow-ros\'}\n\nFrom the root of 2476; TDNT - 7:572 ,1071; masculine noun\n\nAV - cross 28; 28\n\n1) Original idea: upright pile, pillar\n2) crosses\n 2a) A tool known for extreme cruelty and humiliation introduced by the Greeks and Romans by the Phoenicians; it became used in the Roman Empire\n was abolished until the time of Constantine the Great and was applied to heinous criminals, especially slaves from the lowest strata of society, \n Bandits, people who preach or lead rebellions are in every province under occasional circumstances, because of the personal likes and dislikes of the ruling chief, are upright and peaceful\n Shun people, even Roman citizens, were also subjected to this punishment.\n 2b) The punishment of the cross that Christ endured\n 2c) Believers follow the suffering of the crucified Lord',	1),
(6001,	'02264',	'2264 Herodes {hay-ro\'-dace}\n\nheros(\"英雄\")与1491的复合型; 阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Herod, Antipas 27, Herod, the Great 11, Herod Agrippa 6; 44\n\n希律 = \"英勇的\"\n1)希律大帝 (希律一世)\n  纪元前四十年,被罗马议会册封为犹大王.他生性凶残多疑,甚至杀害自己的妻儿,\n  并且因为喜好模仿罗马风俗,课税沉重,因此即使他大力重修圣殿,亦不得犹太人\n  民心.在他执政最后一段时期,耶稣与施洗约翰诞生,也是他下令屠杀伯利恒城两\n  岁以下的男婴.\n2)希律安提帕斯,因着与亲兄弟的妻子希罗底成婚,受约翰谴责,后来受希罗底唆使,\n  将施洗约翰斩首.\n3)希律亚基帕 (#徒 12:1,6,11,19,21|)\n     ',	'2264 Herodes {hay-ro\'-dace}\n\nHeros (“hero”) complex with 1491; positive proper noun\n\nAV - Herod, Antipas 27, Herod, the Great 11, Herod Agrippa 6; 44\n\nherod = “heroic”\n1) Herod the Great (Herod I)\n Forty years before the epoch, he was canonized as King of Judah by the Roman Parliament. He was suspicious of his ferocious nature, and even killed his wife and children,\n And because he likes to imitate Roman customs and is heavily taxed, even if he vigorously rehabilitates the temple, it is forbidden to be a Jew\n The hearts of the people. During the last period of his administration, Jesus and John the Baptist were born, and he also ordered the massacre of the city of Bethlehem 2\n Baby boys under years old.\n2) Herod Antipas, condemned by John for marrying his brother\'s wife Herod, and later instigated by Herod,\n Will decapitate John the Baptist.\n3) Heroia Kippa (#徒 12:1 ,6,11,19,21|)',	1),
(6002,	'02492',	'2492 Iob {ee-obe\'}\n\n源自希伯来文 0347; 阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Job 1; 1\n\n约伯= \"悲痛的哭喊, 哎哟\" 或 \"我要大声疾呼\"\n1) 一位敬神的人, 在试验当中坚忍刚毅, 满有忍耐. \n以其名命名旧约的一书卷, 记载着他的故事. (#雅 5:11|)',	'2492 Iob {ee-obe\'}\n\nDerived from Hebrew 0347; proper noun for masculinity\n\nAV - Job 1; 1\n\nJob = “cry of grief, ouch” or “I\'m going to shout out”\n1) A person who respects God, perseverance and patience during trials. \nNamed after him a volume of the Old Testament, which chronicles his story. (#雅 5:11 |)',	1),
(6003,	'05376',	'5376 Philippos {fil\'-ip-pos}\n\n源自 5384 与 2462;阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Philip (the apostle) 16, Philip (the evangelist) 16,\n     Philip (Herod) 3, Philippi (an adjunct of Caesarea) 2,\n     Philip (the tetrarch) 1; 38\n\n腓力 = \"马的爱好者\"\n1) 基督的一位使徒 (#可 3:18|)\n2) 一位福音使者与耶路撒冷的七位执事之一 (#徒 6:5, 8:5-8, 8:26-35|)\n3) 特拉可尼分封的王, 希律安提帕的兄弟.(同父异母的兄弟)\n   腓力出生于耶路撒冷, 由克丽佩脱拉所生; 马尔赛斯的希律, 一位撒马利亚人: \n   他死于提庇留二十年, 就是在路加福音3章1节所提到年代的五年之后,\n   他曾建立了该撒利亚腓立比. 他同父异母的兄弟希律王安提帕, 非法娶了他的妻子. \n   (Gill)   (#路 3:1,19; 太14:1,3; 可6:17|)\n4) 参看 2542, 该撒利亚腓立比',	'5376 Philippos {fil\'-ip-pos}\n\nDerived from 5384 and 2462; positive proper nouns\n\nAV - Philip (the apostle) 16, Philip (the evangelist) 16,\n Philip (Herod) 3, Philippi (an adjunct of Caesarea) 2,\n Philip (the tetrarch) 1; 38\n\nPhilip = “horse lover”\n1) An Apostle of Christ (#可 3:18 |)\n2) An evangelist and one of the seven deacons in Jerusalem (#徒 6:5, 8:5-8, 8:26-35 |)\n3) King of Traconi, brother of Herod Antipa. (half brother)\n Philip was born in Jerusalem, born of Cleopatra; Herod of Marseis, a Samaritan: \n Twenty years after his death in Tippius, five years after the age mentioned in Luke 3:1,\n He founded Caesarea Philippians. His half-brother Herod Antipa, married his wife illegally. \n (Gill) (#路 3:1 ,19; too 14:1 ,3; can 6:17 |)\n4) See 2542, the Thalia of Philippians',	1),
(6004,	'00078',	'78 Addi {ad-dee\'}\n\n可能源于希伯来文, 参 05716; 阳性专有名词\n\n钦定本 - Addi 1; 1\n\n亚底 = \"装饰\"\n1)哥桑的儿子,麦基的父亲，耶稣基督的家谱(#路 3:28|)',	'78 Addi {ad-dee}\n\nMay be of Hebrew origin, see 05716; positive proper noun\n\nAddi 1; 1\n\nsubtilis = “decoration”\n1) The family tree of Jesus Christ, the son of Godson, McKee\'s father (#路 3:28 |)',	1),
(6005,	'00079',	'79 adelphe {ad-el-fay\'}\n\n源于 80; TDNT - 1:144,22; 阴性名词\n\nAV - sister 24; 24\n\n1) 亲生姐妹\n2) 姐妹\n 2a) 具相同信仰的\n 2b) 群体中关系亲密者\n ',	'79 Adelphe {ad-el-fay\'}\n\nDerived from 80; TDNT - 1:144 ,22; negative noun\n\nAV - sister 24; 24\n\n1) biological sisters\n2) Sisters\n 2a) People of the same faith\n 2b) People with close relationships in the group',	1),
(6006,	'00165',	'165 aion {ahee-ohn\'}\n\n与 104 同源; TDNT - 1:197,31; 阳性名词\n\nAV - ever 71, world 38, never + 3364 + 1519 + 3588 6, evermore 4,\n     age 2, eternal 2, misc 5; 128\n\n1) 一段没有开始与结束的漫长时间\n 1a) 过去, 最早以前\n 1b) 永恒\n2) 历史当中一段时间,时代\n 2a) 现今的时代\n 2b) 将来的时代\n3) 世界\n4) 音译为aeon,被视为一个人(#弗 2:2, 3:9; 西 1:26|) ',	'165 aion {ahee-ohn\'}\n\nHomologous with 104; TDNT - 1:197 ,31; positive noun\n\nAV - ever 71, world 38, never + 3364 + 1519 + 3588 6, evermore 4,\n age 2, Eternal 2, misc 5; 128\n\n1) A long period of time without beginning and ending\n 1a) In the past, before\n 1b) Eternity\n2) A period of time in history, era\n 2a) The present era\n 2b) Future Era\n3) The world\n4) Transliterated as aeon, regarded as a person (#弗 2:2, 3:9; West 1:26 |)',	1),
(6007,	'00490',	'490 Antiocheia {an-tee-okh\'-i-ah}\n\n源自 Antiochus (一名叙利亚王); 专有地名\n\nAV - Antioch 18; 18\n\n安提阿 = \'与之抗衡\"\n1) 叙利亚最大城,亦为西流基帝国的首都,位于Orontes河,为Seleucus Nicanor所\n   建,为纪念其父Antiochus而取名为安提阿.很多希腊化的犹太人住在那里.是该城\n   信徒首先被称为\"基督徒\".\n\n2) 彼西底的一座城,隶属加拉太省,是南加拉太的行政中心,保罗曾数次拜访该城.',	'490 Antiocheia {an-tee-okh\'-i-ah}\n\nDerived from Antiochus (a Syrian king); proprietary place name\n\nAV - Antioch 18; 18\n\nAntioch = \'against it\'\n1) The largest city in Syria, also the capital of the Western Liukian Empire, is located on the Orontes River and is home to Seleucus Nicanor\n It was built and named Antioch in honor of its father, Antiochus. Many Hellenistic Jews lived there. It was the city.\n Believers were first called “Christians”.\n\n2) A city in Pythidi, which is part of the province of Galatia, was the administrative center of South Galatia, and Paul had visited the city several times.',	1),
(6008,	'00575',	'575 apo {apo\'}\n\n基本的质词/语助词; 介系词\n\n钦定本 - from 392, of 129, out of 48, for 10, off 10, by 9, at 9,\n     in 6, since + 3739 5, on 5, not tr. 15, misc. 31; 669\n\n1) (表示与一个地点分开) 从...\n2) (表示起点) 从..., 自从\n3) (表示起源) 来自\n4) (表示自某一点的距离) 离...\n5) (表示因果) 因为, 由于\n6) (作副词) 一致地 (#路 14:18|); 真心地 (#太 18:35|)',	'575 apo {apo\'}\n\nBasic qualified/slang auxiliary words; intermediate words\n\nChinding Book - from 392, of 129, out of 48, for 10, off 10, by 9, at 9,\n in 6, since + 3739 5, on 5, not tr. 15, misc. 31; 669\n\n1) (means separate from one location) from...\n2) (indicates the starting point) from..., since\n3) (denotes origin) from\n4) (indicates the distance from a certain point) away from...\n5) (indicates cause and effect) because, due to\n6) (adverb) unanimously (#路 14:18 |); sincerely (#太 18:35 |)',	1),
(6009,	'05087',	'5087 tithemi {tith\'-ay-mee}\n\n原形theo {theh\'-o}的扩张型 (只用作为某些特定时态的替代字); \nTDNT - 8:152,1176; 动词\n\nAV - lay 28, put 18, lay down 12, make 10, appoint 6,\n     kneel down + 1119 + 3588 5, misc 17; 96\n\n1) 置, 放, 安放于(某个特定地点)\n 1a) 安放,立下\n 1b) 特别的用法\n  1b1) 解释 (#可4:30|)\n  1b2) 放弃,撇下 (特别是在约翰福音)\n  1b3) 表示尊敬 (屈膝, 下跪)\n  1b4) 摆上(服侍) (#约2:10|)\n  1b5) 放在心里\n  1b6) 安排,促成某事 (#太24:51;路12:46;徒27:12|)\n  1b7) (关身语态) 收押\n  1b8) 立下(榜样) (#彼后2:6;罗14:13|)\n2) 积存,储存 (金钱)\n3) 指派, 任命\n4) 设立, 制定, 颁布\n5) (使之经过经验或状况的改变) 使其, 交付给 \n',	'5087 tithemi {tith\'-ay-mee}\n\nthe extended form of the prototype theo {theh\'-o} (used only as a substitute for some specific tenses); \nTDNT - 8:152 ,1176; verb\n\nAV - lay 28, put 18, lay down 12, make 10, put 6,\n kneel down + 1119 + 3588 5, misc 17; 96\n\n1) Place, place, place in (a specific place)\n 1a) Place, stand\n 1b) Special usage\n 1b1) Explain (#可4:30|)\n 1b2) Give up, leave behind (especially in the Gospel of John)\n 1b3) Show respect (kneel, kneel down)\n 1b4) Put on (Serving) (#约2:10|)\n 1b5) Keep it in your heart\n 1b6) Arrange to make something happen (#太24:51; Luke 12:46; Acts 27:12 |)\n 1b7) (closed voice) seizure\n 1b8) Set (Example) (#彼后2:6; Romans 14:13 |)\n2) Store, store (money)\n3) Assignment, Appointment\n4) Establishment, formulation, promulgation\n5) (subject to a change of experience or condition) so that it,',	1),
(6010,	'05777',	'5777 时态 - 简单过去式（译注: 或称过去不定时态, 一般以 \"简过\" 称之）\n\n    梅晨: 简过和不完成式都是指着过去的时间而言, 但是不完成时态是指着过去的\n　　　　　一种进行式的动作, 例: 我过去正在做... ;而简过则译为: 我曾在做....\n          虽然现在时态与现在进行时态没有分别, 但简过的分别却很明显.\n          第一简单过去式和第二简单过去式, 在时间上没有分别, 不过是用两种\n          不同的形态, 造成动词的同一时态.\n\n    简单过去式的特色是强调动作是punctiliar，也就是说，时态并不是强调这个动作\n　　是过去，现在，或未未．在英文中没有相对应的时态，不过通常以简单过去式翻译．\n\n    在文法上，简过代表几种情形，其中较常见的有：指这个行动是由某一时间开始\n　　 (\"inceptive aorist\"), 或者行动终于某一时间 (\"cumulative aorist\")，或者\n　　只是出现在某一个特定的时间  (\"punctiliar aorist\")．\n　　其他的情形，仍可见于希腊文文法中．',	'5777 Tense - Simple Past Tense (translation: or past indefinite tense, generally referred to as “simplified”)\n\n Mei Chen: The simple and unfinished form refer to the past time, but the unfinished tense refers to the past\n A progressive action, for example: I was doing it in the past... ; while the brief translates as: I was doing...\n Although there is no difference between the present tense and the present tense, the difference in brief is clear.\n There is no difference in time between the first simple past and the second simple past, but two\n Different forms, causing the same tense of the verb.\n\n The simple past tense is characterized by emphasizing that the action is punctiliar, that is, the tense does not emphasize the action\n It was in the past, now, or not... there is no corresponding tense in English, but it is usually translated in simple past tense.\n\n Grammatically, the brief represents several situations, the more common of which are: it means that the action began at a certain time\n (“inceptive aorist”), or the action is finally at some point (“inceptive aorist”), or\n It just appears at a specific time (“punctiliar aorist”).\n Other situations can still be found in Greek grammar.',	1),
