(6020,	'01096',	'1096 ginomai {ghin\'-om-ahee}\n\n基本字型, 以关身语态出现; TDNT - 1:681,117; 动词\n\n钦定本 - be 255, come to pass 82, be made 69, be done 63, come 52,\n     become 47, God forbid + 3361 15, arise 13, have 5, be fulfilled 3,\n     be married to 3, be preferred 3, not tr 14, misc 4, vr done 2; 678\n\n1) (自然) 生成\n2) 被制作, 被创造\n3) 升起, 出现, 发展 (事件或现象) \n4) 发生, 成为 (过程或结果)\n5) 变成 (改变进入新的状况)\n6) 迁移\n7) 结果是 (成为某种状态或拥有某些特质)\n8) 出席, 到场\n9) 属于\n10) 在, 在...里面 (一个地方)\n\n   3a) 指出现在公众中的人物\n4) 实行, 完成\n   4a) 行神迹\n5) 变成为, 被做成\n6) 是, 有, 拥有',	'1096 ginomai {ghin\'-om-ahee}\n\nbasic font, in closed voice; TDNT - 1:681 ,117; verb\n\nChinding Book - be 255, come to pass 82, be made 69, be done 63, come 52,\n become 47, God forbid + 3361 15, arise 13, have 5, be surprised 3,\n be married to 3, be preferred 3, not tr 14, misc 4, vr done 2; 678\n\n1) (natural) generation\n2) Be made, be created\n3) rising, appearing, developing (event or phenomenon) \n4) occurs, becomes (process or result)\n5) Become (change into a new state)\n6) Migration\n7) The result is (being in a certain state or possessing certain traits)\n8) Attendance, attendance\n9) Belongs\n10) In, in (one place)\n\n 3a) Point out who is currently in the public\n4) Implementation, completion\n 4a) Miracle\n5) To be made, to be made\n6) Yes, have, own',	1),
(6021,	'02098',	'2098 euaggelion {yoo-ang-ghel\'-ee-on}\n\n与 2097 同源; TDNT - 2:721,267; 中性名词\n\n钦定本 - gospel 46, gospel of Christ 11, gospel of God 7,\n         gospel of the Kingdom 3, misc 10; 77\n\n1) 好消息\n   1a) 喜信, 就是神的国度即将被建立, 其后主耶稣基督的国度也\n       要被建立, 他是这国度的奠基者。耶稣基督死后, 这个词的\n       含义也包括传讲有关于耶稣基督在十字架上受苦受, 带给世\n       人永恒的救恩. 从死里复活, 坐在上帝的右边, 将来要带着\n       荣耀再现, 建立永远的国度.\n   1b) 藉着耶稣基督得着救恩的好消息\n   1c) 宣布上帝的恩典已在耶稣基督里显明, 信者得享在基督里\n   1d) 福音\n   1e) 耶稣基督所言, 所行, 及其受死证明他是弥赛亚, 他的\n　　　 言行、受死的故事被称为福音或喜信.',	'2098 euaggelion {yoo-ang-ghel \'-ee-on}\n\nSame as 2097; TDNT - 2:721 ,267; neutral noun\n\nConfirmation Book - Gospel 46, Gospel of Christ 11, Gospel of God 7,\n Gospel of the Kingdom 3, misc 10; 77\n\n1) Good news\n 1a) Good faith, that is, the kingdom of God is about to be established, and then the kingdom of the Lord Jesus Christ\n To be established, he was the founder of this country. After the death of Jesus Christ, the word\n The meaning also includes preaching about the suffering of Jesus Christ on the Cross, brought to the world\n The eternal salvation of man. Resurrected from the dead, sitting at the right hand of God, to be carried in the future\n Glory reappears, and the eternal kingdom is built.\n 1b) Good news of salvation through Jesus Christ\n 1c) Declare that God\'s grace has been revealed in Jesus Christ and that believers may enjoy it in Christ\n 1d) Gospel\n 1e) The words, deeds, and death of Jesus Christ prove that He is the Messiah, his\n The story of words and deeds and death is called the gospel or happy faith.',	1),
(6022,	'02501',	'2501 Ioseph {ee-o-safe\'}\n\n源于希伯来字 03130;阳性专有名词\n\nAV - Joseph (husband of Mary) 16, Joseph (son of Jacob) 9,\n     Joseph of Arimathaea 6, Joseph (son of Judas) 1,\n     Joseph of Barsabas 1, Joseph son of Jonan 1,\n     Joseph (son of Mattathias) 1; 35\n\n约瑟 = \"任他增添\"\n1) 族长之一, 雅各的第十一个儿子\n2) 约南的儿子, 基督的祖先之一(#路 3:30|)\n3) 犹大的儿子, 耶稣的另一个祖先(#路 3:26|)\n4) 玛他提亚的儿子, 另一位基督的祖先(#路 3:25|)\n5) 耶稣的母亲马利亚的丈夫 (#太 1:16|)\n6) 耶稣的兄弟约西 (#太 13:55|)\n7) 亚利马太的约瑟, 公会中的人, 是支持耶稣的人 (#太 27:57,59;可 15:43,45|)\n8) 被称作巴拿巴的约瑟 (#徒 4:36|)\n9) 称为巴撒巴的约瑟, 又叫作犹七都 (#徒 1:23|)',	'2501 Ioseph {ee-o-safe\'}\n\nDerived from the Hebrew word 03130; masculine proper noun\n\nAV - Joseph (husband of Mary) 16, Joseph (son of Jacob) 9,\n Joseph of Arimathaea 6, Joseph (son of Judas) 1,\n Joseph of Barsabas 1, Joseph son of Jonan 1,\n Joseph (son of Mattathias) 1; 35\n\njoser = “let him add”\n1) One of the patriarchs, the eleventh son of Jacob\n2) Son of Jonan, one of the ancestors of Christ (#路 3:30 |)\n3) Son of Judah, another ancestor of Jesus (#路 3:26 |)\n4) Son of Matthias, ancestor of another Christ (#路 3:25 |)\n5) The husband of Mary, the mother of Jesus (#太 1:16 |)\n6) Joseph, Jesus\' brother (#太 13:55 |)\n7) Joseph of Arima, a man in the guild, was a supporter of Jesus (#太 27:57 ,59; May 15:43 ,45|)\n8) Known as Joseph of Barnabas (#徒 4:36 |)\n9) Joseph called Basabba, also known as the Seven Cities of Judah (#徒 1:23 |)',	1),
(6023,	'03056',	'3056 logos {log\'-os}\n\n源自 03004; TDNT - 4:69,505; 阳性名词\n\n钦定本 - word 218, saying 50, account 8, speech 8, Word (Christ) 7,\n     thing 5, not tr 2, misc 32; 330\n\n1) 话语\n   1a) 口头的\n       1a1) (用来表达的) 言语\n       1a2) 其他形式的言语表达: 论述, 问题, 内容, 宣告, 指示, 教导, 神的话\n       1a3) 一篇演说, 声言, 宣言\n   1b) 文字的\n   1c) 论述\n2) 只用在与心思有关的方面\n   2a) 理智, 思考的心理机能, 默想, 推论的, 慎思的\n   2b) 理由, 亦即: 考量, 考虑\n   2c) 原因, 亦即: 计算, 根据\n   2d) 陈述, 亦即: 关于审判而提出的答辩或解释\n   2e) 关联, 亦即: 以我们与其的关系来判断\n       2e1) 推论如此\n   2f) 理由, 动机, 根据\n3) 在约翰福音中, 是指神的话; 基督耶稣与神联合的智慧和能力;\n   他在宇宙中创造和治理的职事; 是世上物质和道德生命力的起因;\n   是为了人类的救恩而穿上人类本性, 在耶稣的形体里的弥赛亚;\n   是神性中的第二位格, 并从他的话和行为中显着地的表明出来.',	'3056 logos {log\'-os}\n\nFrom 03004; TDNT - 4:69 ,505; positive noun\n\nConclusion - word 218, saying 50, account 8, speech 8, word (Christ) 7,\n thing 5, not tr 2, misc 32; 330\n\n1) Discourse\n 1a) Oral\n 1a1) words (used to express)\n 1a2) Other forms of verbal expression: discourse, question, content, proclamation, instruction, teaching, word of God\n 1a3) A speech, a statement, a declaration\n 1b) literal\n 1c) Discussion\n2) Only used in areas related to the mind\n 2a) Sane, the mental function of thinking, meditating, reasoning, prudent\n 2b) reasons, namely: consideration, consideration\n 2c) the reason, ie: calculation, according to\n 2d) statement, that is, a reply or explanation given in connection with the trial\n 2e) association, that is, judging by our relationship to it\n 2e1) Inference is so\n 2f) Rationale, motive, based\n3) In the Gospel of John, refers to the word of God; the wisdom and power of Christ Jesus in union with God;\n His ministry of creation and governance in the universe; the cause of the material and moral vitality of the world;\n Wear human nature for the salvation of mankind, the Messiah in the form of Jesus;\n is the second person in divinity, and is evident from his words and deeds.',	1),
(6024,	'03962',	'3962 pater {pat-ayr\'}\n\n显然为字根; TDNT - 5:945,805; 阳性名词\n\nAV - Father 268, father 150; 419\n\n1) 生育者或男性先祖\n   1a) 较近的先祖: 肉身的父亲, 身生的父亲, 或双亲\n   1b) 较远的先祖: 宗族或支派的创始者, 一个民族的始祖, 祖宗: 亚伯拉罕\n       被称为是雅各和大卫的先祖\n       1b1) 父亦即先祖, 祖宗, 一个国家的创始者\n   1c) 年纪较长的人, 长者\n2) 隐喻\n   2a) 任何事物的开山始祖及传达者\n       2a1) 一个家族, 或是由和自己有同样理念的人士所组成的团体之创始人\n       2a2) 将自己的理念灌输给他人, 激励且管理他们的想法的人\n   2b) 一个处于父亲的地位且以亲职照顾他人的人\n   2c) 尊敬的称呼\n       2c1) 老师, 当其弟子回顾得自他的知识和训练时, 所用的称呼\n       2c2) 犹太教议会/公会中的成员, 以其智慧及专才,使他人得益\n 3) 上帝被称为天父\n   3a) 因为他是星宿, 天上之的太阳和月亮的创造者, 支持者, 和管理者\n   3b) 因为他是凡有理性, 有智慧者的创造者, 保存者, 守护者, 保护者,\n       无论是天使或人类    \n       3b1) 凡有灵的生命的和所有人类的父\n   3c) 他是每位基督徒的父亲, 藉着基督得与上帝有特别亲近, 且亲密的关系, \n       并且不再害怕自已是罪人, 会受到神的严厉的审判, 反倒尊敬他, 是已\n       与自己和好的亲爱父亲.\n   3d) 他是耶稣基督的父, 他是以爱和父联合, 且有亲密的关系, 明白天父的旨意者, \n       被指派去解释和执行神拯救世人的计画, 也和世人分享自己的神性.\n        3d1) 藉由耶稣基督他自己\n        3d2) 藉由使徒\n',	'3962 pater {pat-ayr\'}\n\nApparently root; TDNT - 5:945 ,805; masculine noun\n\nAV - Father 268, father 150; 419\n\n1) The person who gave birth or male ancestor\n 1a) Closer ancestor: the father in the flesh, the biological father, or both parents\n 1b) Distant ancestor: founder of a clan or tribe, ancestor of a people, ancestor: Abraham\n Known to be the ancestor of Jacob and David\n 1b1) The father is the ancestor, the ancestor, the founder of a nation\n 1c) The older person, the elder\n2) Metaphors\n 2a) The founder and communicator of anything\n 2a1) The founder of a family, or a group of people who share the same ideas as themselves\n 2a2) People who instill their ideas in others, motivate and manage their ideas\n 2b) A person who is in the position of a father and takes care of others by his family\n 2c) Respectful title\n 2c1) The term used by a teacher when his disciple recalls his knowledge and training\n 2c2) Members of the Rabbinical Assembly/Guild who, with their wisdom and expertise, benefit others\n 3) God is called Heavenly Father\n 3a) Because he is the creator, supporter, and manager of the stars and stars, the sun and moon in the heavens\n 3b) For he is the creator, preserver, guardian, protector, protector of all rational and wise men,\n Whether it\'s an angel or a human \n 3b1) Where there is spiritual life and the father of all human beings\n 3c) He is the father of every Christian, and through Christ he has a special closeness and close relationship with God, \n And no longer afraid that he is a sinner, will be judged harshly by God, but will respect him instead.\n With myself and good dear father.\n 3d) He is the Father of Jesus Christ, who is united with the Father in love, has a close relationship, understands the will of the Father, \n Assigned to explain and implement God\'s plan to save the world, and to share his divinity with the world.\n 3d1) Through Jesus Christ Himself\n 3d2) Through the Apostle',	1),
(6025,	'05440',	'5440 phulakterion {foo-lak-tay\'-ree-on}\n\n由 5442 衍生的中性词 ; 中性名词\n\nAV - phylactery 1; 1\n\n1) 祷告带, 祷告匣 (#太 23:5|)\n 1a)犹太人用这个字来描述细长的羊皮卷上记载下列摩西律法的经文\n   \"出 13:1-10, 11-16; 申 6:4-9,11:13-21\"  而且这羊皮卷被收藏在子盒里. \n   他们习惯在祷告时, 用皮带系紧在前额, 以及靠在心部位的左臂上,为的是\n   慎重提醒自己, 有责任在额头上及在心上保持神的诫命, 这是依据在出 13:16, \n   申 6:8, 11:18所给予的指示.这些卷轴被认为是有能力的, 像护身符一样, \n   可以防止各类恶者及驱魔.法利赛人习惯把经卷扩大以引人注目, 以显出他们比\n   大多数的人更渴慕被神的律法提醒.',	'5440 phulakterion {foo-lak-tay\'-ree-on}\n\nNeutral words derived from 5442; neutral nouns\n\nAV - phylactery 1; 1\n\n1) Prayer Belt, Prayer Box (#太 23:5 |)\n 1a) The Jews used this word to describe the scriptures on the slender sheepskin roll that recorded the following Moses\n “Out 13:1-10, 11-16; Sheen 6:4-9, 11:13-21” And this parchment was collected in a sub-box. \n They are used to wearing belts tied to their foreheads while praying, and leaning on their left arm at the heart, in order to\n Carefully remind yourself of your responsibility to keep God\'s commandments on your forehead and in your heart, according to Exodus 13:16, \n Instructions given by Shen 6:8, 11:18. These scrolls are considered capable and, like talismans, \n It can prevent all kinds of evils and exorcisms. The Pharisees have a habit of expanding the scriptures to draw attention to their comparison.\n Most people are more eager to be reminded by God\'s law.',	1);
